  <Name>k__BackingField: Matthew
  fancyName: 
  nickname: mat
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 433894a244f646848a22a9c7d127b66b, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ancestors of Jesus the Messiah'
      title: The Ancestors of Jesus the Messiah
      number: 1
      content: '  This is a record of the ancestors of Jesus the Messiah, a descendant
        of David and of Abraham[[COMMENT(0)]]:  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:1 '
        content: Greek <b>Jesus the Messiah, Son of David and son of Abraham.</b>
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Abraham was the father of Isaac.Isaac was the father of Jacob.Jacob
        was the father of Judah and his brothers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Judah was the father of Perez and Zerah (whose mother was Tamar).Perez
        was the father of Hezron.Hezron was the father of Ram.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:3 '
        content: Greek <b>Aram, </b>a variant spelling of Ram; also in 1:4. See 1
          Chr 2:9-10.
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Ram was the father of Amminadab.Amminadab was the father of Nahshon.Nahshon
        was the father of Salmon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Salmon was the father of Boaz (whose mother was Rahab).Boaz was the
        father of Obed (whose mother was Ruth).Obed was the father of Jesse.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Jesse was the father of King David.David was the father of Solomon
        (whose mother was Bathsheba, the widow of Uriah).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Solomon was the father of Rehoboam.Rehoboam was the father of Abijah.Abijah
        was the father of Asa.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:7 '
        content: Greek <b>Asaph, </b>a variant spelling of Asa; also in 1:8. See
          1 Chr 3:10.
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Asa was the father of Jehoshaphat.Jehoshaphat was the father of Jehoram.[[COMMENT(0)]]Jehoram
        was the father[[COMMENT(1)]] of Uzziah.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:8a '
        content: Greek <b>Joram, </b>a variant spelling of Jehoram; also in 1:8b.
          See 1 Kgs 22:50 and note at 1 Chr 3:11.
      - number: '1:8b '
        content: Or <b>ancestor; </b>also in 1:11.
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Uzziah was the father of Jotham.Jotham was the father of Ahaz.Ahaz
        was the father of Hezekiah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Hezekiah was the father of Manasseh.Manasseh was the father of Amon.[[COMMENT(0)]]Amon
        was the father of Josiah.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:10 '
        content: Greek <b>Amos, </b>a variant spelling of Amon; also in 1:10b. See
          1 Chr 3:14.
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Josiah was the father of Jehoiachin[[COMMENT(0)]] and his brothers
        (born at the time of the exile to Babylon).  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:11 '
        content: Greek <b>Jeconiah, </b>a variant spelling of Jehoiachin; also in
          1:12. See 2 Kgs 24:6 and note at 1 Chr 3:16.
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'After the Babylonian exile:Jehoiachin was the father of Shealtiel.Shealtiel
        was the father of Zerubbabel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Zerubbabel was the father of Abiud.Abiud was the father of Eliakim.Eliakim
        was the father of Azor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Azor was the father of Zadok.Zadok was the father of Akim.Akim was
        the father of Eliud.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Eliud was the father of Eleazar.Eleazar was the father of Matthan.Matthan
        was the father of Jacob.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Jacob was the father of Joseph, the husband of Mary.Mary gave birth
        to Jesus, who is called the Messiah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: The Birth of Jesus the Messiah'
      title: The Birth of Jesus the Messiah
      number: 17
      content: 'All those listed above include fourteen generations from Abraham
        to David, fourteen from David to the Babylonian exile, and fourteen from
        the Babylonian exile to the Messiah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'This is how Jesus the Messiah was born. His mother, Mary, was engaged
        to be married to Joseph. But before the marriage took place, while she was
        still a virgin, she became pregnant through the power of the Holy Spirit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Joseph, to whom she was engaged, was a righteous man and did not
        want to disgrace her publicly, so he decided to break the engagement[[COMMENT(0)]]
        quietly.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:19 '
        content: Greek <b>to divorce her.</b>
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "As he considered this, an angel of the Lord appeared to him in a
        dream. \u201CJoseph, son of David,\u201D the angel said, \u201Cdo not be
        afraid to take Mary as your wife. For the child within her was conceived
        by the Holy Spirit. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And she will have a son, and you are to name him Jesus,[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>
        for he will save his people from their sins.\u201D</smallcaps>  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:21 '
        content: "<b>Jesus </b>means \u201CThe <span class=\"ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf\">Lord</span>
          saves.\u201D"
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "All of this occurred to fulfill the Lord\u2019s message through his
        prophet:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CLook! The virgin will conceive a child!She will give birth
        to a son,and they will call him Immanuel,[[COMMENT(0)]]which means \u2018God
        is with us.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:23 '
        content: Isa 7:14; 8:8, 10 (Greek version).
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When Joseph woke up, he did as the angel of the Lord commanded and
        took Mary as his wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: But he did not have sexual relations with her until her son was born.
        And Joseph named him Jesus.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Visitors from the East'
      title: Visitors from the East
      number: 1
      content: '  Jesus was born in Bethlehem in Judea, during the reign of King
        Herod. About that time some wise men[[COMMENT(0)]] from eastern lands arrived
        in Jerusalem, asking, '
      comments:
      - number: '2:1 '
        content: Or <b>royal astrologers; </b>Greek reads <b>magi; </b>also in 2:7,
          16.
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CWhere is the newborn king of the Jews? We saw his star as it
        rose,[[COMMENT(0)]] and we have come to worship him.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:2 '
        content: Or <b>star in the east.</b>
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'King Herod was deeply disturbed when he heard this, as was everyone
        in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "He called a meeting of the leading priests and teachers of religious
        law and asked, \u201CWhere is the Messiah supposed to be born?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CIn Bethlehem in Judea,\u201D they said, \u201Cfor this is what
        the prophet wrote:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u2018And you, O Bethlehem in the land of Judah,are not least among
        the ruling cities[[COMMENT(0)]] of Judah,for a ruler will come from youwho
        will be the shepherd for my people Israel.\u2019[[COMMENT(1)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:6a '
        content: Greek <b>the rulers.</b>
      - number: '2:6b '
        content: Mic 5:2; 2 Sam 5:2.
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then Herod called for a private meeting with the wise men, and he
        learned from them the time when the star first appeared. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then he told them, \u201CGo to Bethlehem and search carefully for
        the child. And when you find him, come back and tell me so that I can go
        and worship him, too!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'After this interview the wise men went their way. And the star they
        had seen in the east guided them to Bethlehem. It went ahead of them and
        stopped over the place where the child was. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When they saw the star, they were filled with joy! '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They entered the house and saw the child with his mother, Mary, and
        they bowed down and worshiped him. Then they opened their treasure chests
        and gave him gifts of gold, frankincense, and myrrh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Escape to Egypt'
      title: The Escape to Egypt
      number: 12
      content: 'When it was time to leave, they returned to their own country by
        another route, for God had warned them in a dream not to return to Herod.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "After the wise men were gone, an angel of the Lord appeared to Joseph
        in a dream. \u201CGet up! Flee to Egypt with the child and his mother,\u201D
        the angel said. \u201CStay there until I tell you to return, because Herod
        is going to search for the child to kill him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'That night Joseph left for Egypt with the child and Mary, his mother, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "and they stayed there until Herod\u2019s death. This fulfilled what
        the Lord had spoken through the prophet: \u201CI called my Son out of Egypt.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:15 '
        content: Hos 11:1.
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Herod was furious when he realized that the wise men had outwitted
        him. He sent soldiers to kill all the boys in and around Bethlehem who were
        two years old and under, based on the wise men\u2019s report of the star\u2019s
        first appearance. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Herod\u2019s brutal action fulfilled what God had spoken through
        the prophet Jeremiah:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: The Return to Nazareth'
      title: The Return to Nazareth
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CA cry was heard in Ramah\u2014weeping and great mourning.Rachel
        weeps for her children,refusing to be comforted,for they are dead.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:18 '
        content: Jer 31:15.
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'When Herod died, an angel of the Lord appeared in a dream to Joseph
        in Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CGet up!\u201D the angel said. \u201CTake the child and his
        mother back to the land of Israel, because those who were trying to kill
        the child are dead.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So Joseph got up and returned to the land of Israel with Jesus and
        his mother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But when he learned that the new ruler of Judea was Herod\u2019s
        son Archelaus, he was afraid to go there. Then, after being warned in a dream,
        he left for the region of Galilee. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So the family went and lived in a town called Nazareth. This fulfilled
        what the prophets had said: \u201CHe will be called a Nazarene.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: John the Baptist Prepares the Way'
      title: John the Baptist Prepares the Way
      number: 1
      content: '  In those days John the Baptist came to the Judean wilderness and
        began preaching. His message was, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CRepent of your sins and turn to God, for the Kingdom of Heaven
        is near.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '3:2 '
        content: Or <b>has come, </b>or <b>is coming soon.</b>
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The prophet Isaiah was speaking about John when he said,\u201CHe
        is a voice shouting in the wilderness,\u2018Prepare the way for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        coming!Clear the road for him!\u2019\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:3 '
        content: Isa 40:3 (Greek version).
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "John\u2019s clothes were woven from coarse camel hair, and he wore
        a leather belt around his waist. For food he ate locusts and wild honey. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'People from Jerusalem and from all of Judea and all over the Jordan
        Valley went out to see and hear John. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And when they confessed their sins, he baptized them in the Jordan
        River.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But when he saw many Pharisees and Sadducees coming to watch him
        baptize,[[COMMENT(0)]] he denounced them. \u201CYou brood of snakes!\u201D
        he exclaimed. \u201CWho warned you to flee the coming wrath? "
      comments:
      - number: '3:7 '
        content: Or <b>coming to be baptized.</b>
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Prove by the way you live that you have repented of your sins and
        turned to God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Don\u2019t just say to each other, \u2018We\u2019re safe, for we
        are descendants of Abraham.\u2019 That means nothing, for I tell you, God
        can create children of Abraham from these very stones. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Even now the ax of God\u2019s judgment is poised, ready to sever
        the roots of the trees. Yes, every tree that does not produce good fruit
        will be chopped down and thrown into the fire.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CI baptize with[[COMMENT(0)]] water those who repent of their
        sins and turn to God. But someone is coming soon who is greater than I am\u2014so
        much greater that I\u2019m not worthy even to be his slave and carry his
        sandals. He will baptize you with the Holy Spirit and with fire.[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:11a '
        content: Or <b>in.</b>
      - number: '3:11b '
        content: Or <b>in the Holy Spirit and in fire.</b>
    - name: '12: The Baptism of Jesus'
      title: The Baptism of Jesus
      number: 12
      content: "He is ready to separate the chaff from the wheat with his winnowing
        fork. Then he will clean up the threshing area, gathering the wheat into
        his barn but burning the chaff with never-ending fire.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then Jesus went from Galilee to the Jordan River to be baptized by
        John. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But John tried to talk him out of it. \u201CI am the one who needs
        to be baptized by you,\u201D he said, \u201Cso why are you coming to me?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CIt should be done, for we must carry
        out all that God requires.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>\u201D</JESUS> So
        John agreed to baptize him.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:15 '
        content: Or <b>for we must fulfill all righteousness.</b>
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'After his baptism, as Jesus came up out of the water, the heavens
        were opened[[COMMENT(0)]] and he saw the Spirit of God descending like a
        dove and settling on him. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:16 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>opened to him.</b>
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And a voice from heaven said, \u201CThis is my dearly loved Son,
        who brings me great joy.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Temptation of Jesus'
      title: The Temptation of Jesus
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Jesus was led by the Spirit into the wilderness to be tempted
        there by the devil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For forty days and forty nights he fasted and became very hungry.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "During that time the devil[[COMMENT(0)]] came and said to him, \u201CIf
        you are the Son of God, tell these stones to become loaves of bread.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:3 '
        content: 'Greek <b>the tempter.</b>  '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But Jesus told him, <JESUS>\u201CNo! The Scriptures say,</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>\u2018People do not live by bread alone,</JESUS>  <JESUS>but by every
        word that comes from the mouth of God.\u2019</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:4 '
        content: '  Deut 8:3.  '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the devil took him to the holy city, Jerusalem, to the highest
        point of the Temple, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "and said, \u201CIf you are the Son of God, jump off! For the Scriptures
        say,\u2018He will order his angels to protect you.And they will hold you
        up with their handsso you won\u2019t even hurt your foot on a stone.\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:6 '
        content: Ps 91:11-12.
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CThe Scriptures also say, \u2018You
        must not test the </JESUS><smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:7 '
        content: 'Deut 6:16.  '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Next the devil took him to the peak of a very high mountain and showed
        him all the kingdoms of the world and their glory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CI will give it all to you,\u201D he said, \u201Cif you will
        kneel down and worship me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CGet out of here, Satan,\u201D </JESUS>Jesus told him.
        <JESUS>\u201CFor the Scriptures say,</JESUS>  <JESUS>\u2018You must worship
        the </JESUS><smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God  <JESUS>and serve only him.\u2019</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:10 '
        content: '  Deut 6:13.  '
    - name: '11: The Ministry of Jesus Begins'
      title: The Ministry of Jesus Begins
      number: 11
      content: 'Then the devil went away, and angels came and took care of Jesus.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When Jesus heard that John had been arrested, he left Judea and returned
        to Galilee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He went first to Nazareth, then left there and moved to Capernaum,
        beside the Sea of Galilee, in the region of Zebulun and Naphtali. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'This fulfilled what God said through the prophet Isaiah:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CIn the land of Zebulun and of Naphtali,beside the sea, beyond
        the Jordan River,in Galilee where so many Gentiles live,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "the people who sat in darknesshave seen a great light.And for those
        who lived in the land where death casts its shadow,a light has shined.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:15-16 '
        content: Isa 9:1-2 (Greek version).
    - name: '17: The First Disciples'
      title: The First Disciples
      number: 17
      content: "From then on Jesus began to preach, <JESUS>\u201CRepent of your sins
        and turn to God, for the Kingdom of Heaven is near.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:17 '
        content: Or <b>has come, </b>or <b>is coming soon.</b>
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "One day as Jesus was walking along the shore of the Sea of Galilee,
        he saw two brothers\u2014Simon, also called Peter, and Andrew\u2014throwing
        a net into the water, for they fished for a living. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Jesus called out to them, <JESUS>\u201CCome, follow me, and I will
        show you how to fish for people!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And they left their nets at once and followed him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'A little farther up the shore he saw two other brothers, James and
        John, sitting in a boat with their father, Zebedee, repairing their nets.
        And he called them to come, too. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Crowds Follow Jesus'
      title: Crowds Follow Jesus
      number: 22
      content: 'They immediately followed him, leaving the boat and their father
        behind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Jesus traveled throughout the region of Galilee, teaching in the
        synagogues and announcing the Good News about the Kingdom. And he healed
        every kind of disease and illness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "News about him spread as far as Syria, and people soon began bringing
        to him all who were sick. And whatever their sickness or disease, or if they
        were demon possessed or epileptic or paralyzed\u2014he healed them all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Large crowds followed him wherever he went\u2014people from Galilee,
        the Ten Towns,[[COMMENT(0)]] Jerusalem, from all over Judea, and from east
        of the Jordan River."
      comments:
      - number: '4:25 '
        content: Greek <b>Decapolis.</b>
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Sermon on the Mount'
      title: The Sermon on the Mount
      number: 1
      content: '  One day as he saw the crowds gathering, Jesus went up on the mountainside
        and sat down. His disciples gathered around him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: The Beatitudes'
      title: The Beatitudes
      number: 2
      content: 'and he began to teach them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CGod blesses those who are poor and realize their need
        for him,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>for the Kingdom of Heaven is theirs.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:3 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>poor in spirit.</b>    '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  <JESUS>God blesses those who mourn,</JESUS>  <JESUS>for they will
        be comforted.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  <JESUS>God blesses those who are humble,</JESUS>  <JESUS>for they
        will inherit the whole earth.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  <JESUS>God blesses those who hunger and thirst for justice,</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>for they will be satisfied.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:6 '
        content: '  Or   <b>for righteousness.</b>    '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  <JESUS>God blesses those who are merciful,</JESUS>  <JESUS>for
        they will be shown mercy.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  <JESUS>God blesses those whose hearts are pure,</JESUS>  <JESUS>for
        they will see God.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  <JESUS>God blesses those who work for peace,</JESUS>  <JESUS>for
        they will be called the children of God.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  <JESUS>God blesses those who are persecuted for doing right,</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>for the Kingdom of Heaven is theirs.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CGod blesses you when people mock you and persecute
        you and lie about you and say all sorts of evil things against you because
        you are my followers.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Teaching about Salt and Light'
      title: Teaching about Salt and Light
      number: 12
      content: '<JESUS>Be happy about it! Be very glad! For a great reward awaits
        you in heaven. And remember, the ancient prophets were persecuted in the
        same way.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CYou are the salt of the earth. But what good is salt
        if it has lost its flavor? Can you make it salty again? It will be thrown
        out and trampled underfoot as worthless.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CYou are the light of the world\u2014like a city on
        a hilltop that cannot be hidden.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '<JESUS>No one lights a lamp and then puts it under a basket. Instead,
        a lamp is placed on a stand, where it gives light to everyone in the house.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Teaching about the Law'
      title: Teaching about the Law
      number: 16
      content: '<JESUS>In the same way, let your good deeds shine out for all to
        see, so that everyone will praise your heavenly Father.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t misunderstand why I have come. I did not
        come to abolish the law of Moses or the writings of the prophets. No, I came
        to accomplish their purpose.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>I tell you the truth, until heaven and earth disappear, not
        even the smallest detail of God\u2019s law will disappear until its purpose
        is achieved.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>So if you ignore the least commandment and teach others to
        do the same, you will be called the least in the Kingdom of Heaven. But anyone
        who obeys God\u2019s laws and teaches them will be called great in the Kingdom
        of Heaven.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Teaching about Anger'
      title: Teaching about Anger
      number: 20
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBut I warn you\u2014unless your righteousness is better
        than the righteousness of the teachers of religious law and the Pharisees,
        you will never enter the Kingdom of Heaven!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CYou have heard that our ancestors were told, \u2018You
        must not murder. If you commit murder, you are subject to judgment.\u2019</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:21 '
        content: '  Exod 20:13; Deut 5:17.  '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '<JESUS>But I say, if you are even angry with someone,</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>you are subject to judgment! If you call someone an idiot,</JESUS>[[COMMENT(1)]] 
        <JESUS>you are in danger of being brought before the court. And if you curse
        someone,</JESUS>[[COMMENT(2)]]  <JESUS>you are in danger of the fires of
        hell.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(3)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:22a '
        content: Some manuscripts add <b>without cause.</b>
      - number: '5:22b '
        content: "Greek uses an Aramaic term of contempt: <b>If you say to your brother,
          \u2018Raca.\u2019</b>"
      - number: '5:22c '
        content: "Greek <b>if you say, \u2018You fool.\u2019</b>"
      - number: '5:22d '
        content: 'Greek <b>Gehenna; </b>also in 5:29, 30.  '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CSo if you are presenting a sacrifice</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>at the altar in the Temple and you suddenly remember that someone
        has something against you,</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:23 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>gift; </b>  also in 5:24.  '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '<JESUS>leave your sacrifice there at the altar. Go and be reconciled
        to that person. Then come and offer your sacrifice to God.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CWhen you are on the way to court with your adversary,
        settle your differences quickly. Otherwise, your accuser may hand you over
        to the judge, who will hand you over to an officer, and you will be thrown
        into prison.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Teaching about Adultery'
      title: Teaching about Adultery
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>And if that happens, you surely won\u2019t be free again until
        you have paid the last penny.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:26 '
        content: 'Greek <b>the last kodrantes </b>[i.e., quadrans].  '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CYou have heard the commandment that says, \u2018You
        must not commit adultery.\u2019</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:27 '
        content: '  Exod 20:14; Deut 5:18.  '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '<JESUS>But I say, anyone who even looks at a woman with lust has
        already committed adultery with her in his heart.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "<JESUS>So if your eye\u2014even your good eye</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>\u2014causes
        you to lust, gouge it out and throw it away. It is better for you to lose
        one part of your body than for your whole body to be thrown into hell.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:29 '
        content: Greek <b>your right eye.</b>
    - name: '30: Teaching about Divorce'
      title: Teaching about Divorce
      number: 30
      content: "<JESUS>And if your hand\u2014even your stronger hand</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>\u2014causes
        you to sin, cut it off and throw it away. It is better for you to lose one
        part of your body than for your whole body to be thrown into hell.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:30 '
        content: 'Greek <b>your right hand.</b>  '
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CYou have heard the law that says, \u2018A man can
        divorce his wife by merely giving her a written notice of divorce.\u2019</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:31 '
        content: '  Deut 24:1.    '
    - name: '32: Teaching about Vows'
      title: Teaching about Vows
      number: 32
      content: '<JESUS>But I say that a man who divorces his wife, unless she has
        been unfaithful, causes her to commit adultery. And anyone who marries a
        divorced woman also commits adultery.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CYou have also heard that our ancestors were told,
        \u2018You must not break your vows; you must carry out the vows you make
        to the </JESUS><smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:33 '
        content: '  Num 30:2.    '
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "<JESUS>But I say, do not make any vows! Do not say, \u2018By heaven!\u2019
        because heaven is God\u2019s throne.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "<JESUS>And do not say, \u2018By the earth!\u2019 because the earth
        is his footstool. And do not say, \u2018By Jerusalem!\u2019 for Jerusalem
        is the city of the great King.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "<JESUS>Do not even say, \u2018By my head!\u2019 for you can\u2019t
        turn one hair white or black.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: Teaching about Revenge'
      title: Teaching about Revenge
      number: 37
      content: "<JESUS>Just say a simple, \u2018Yes, I will,\u2019 or \u2018No, I
        won\u2019t.\u2019 Anything beyond this is from the evil one.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CYou have heard the law that says the punishment must
        match the injury: \u2018An eye for an eye, and a tooth for a tooth.\u2019</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:38 '
        content: "  Greek   <b>the law that says: \u2018An eye for an eye and a tooth
          for a tooth.\u2019 </b>  Exod 21:24; Lev 24:20; Deut 19:21.  "
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: '<JESUS>But I say, do not resist an evil person! If someone slaps
        you on the right cheek, offer the other cheek also.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: '<JESUS>If you are sued in court and your shirt is taken from you,
        give your coat, too.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: '<JESUS>If a soldier demands that you carry his gear for a mile,</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>carry it two miles.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:41 '
        content: 'Greek <b>milion </b>[4,854 feet or 1,478 meters].  '
    - name: '42: Teaching about Love for Enemies'
      title: Teaching about Love for Enemies
      number: 42
      content: "<JESUS>Give to those who ask, and don\u2019t turn away from those
        who want to borrow.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CYou have heard the law that says, \u2018Love your
        neighbor\u2019</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and hate your enemy.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:43 '
        content: '  Lev 19:18.  '
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: '<JESUS>But I say, love your enemies!</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>Pray
        for those who persecute you!</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:44 '
        content: Some manuscripts add <b>Bless those who curse you. Do good to those
          who hate you. </b>Compare Luke 6:27-28.
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: '<JESUS>In that way, you will be acting as true children of your Father
        in heaven. For he gives his sunlight to both the evil and the good, and he
        sends rain on the just and the unjust alike.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: '<JESUS>If you love only those who love you, what reward is there
        for that? Even corrupt tax collectors do that much.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: '<JESUS>If you are kind only to your friends,</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>how are you different from anyone else? Even pagans do that.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:47 '
        content: Greek <b>your brothers.</b>
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: <JESUS>But you are to be perfect, even as your Father in heaven is
        perfect.</JESUS>
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Teaching about Giving to the Needy'
      title: Teaching about Giving to the Needy
      number: 1
      content: "    <JESUS>\u201CWatch out! Don\u2019t do your good deeds publicly,
        to be admired by others, for you will lose the reward from your Father in
        heaven.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "<JESUS>When you give to someone in need, don\u2019t do as the hypocrites
        do\u2014blowing trumpets in the synagogues and streets to call attention
        to their acts of charity! I tell you the truth, they have received all the
        reward they will ever get.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "<JESUS>But when you give to someone in need, don\u2019t let your
        left hand know what your right hand is doing.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Teaching about Prayer and Fasting'
      title: Teaching about Prayer and Fasting
      number: 4
      content: '<JESUS>Give your gifts in private, and your Father, who sees everything,
        will reward you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CWhen you pray, don\u2019t be like the hypocrites who
        love to pray publicly on street corners and in the synagogues where everyone
        can see them. I tell you the truth, that is all the reward they will ever
        get.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '<JESUS>But when you pray, go away by yourself, shut the door behind
        you, and pray to your Father in private. Then your Father, who sees everything,
        will reward you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CWhen you pray, don\u2019t babble on and on as the
        Gentiles do. They think their prayers are answered merely by repeating their
        words again and again.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>Don\u2019t be like them, for your Father knows exactly what
        you need even before you ask him!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '<JESUS>Pray like this:</JESUS>  <JESUS>Our Father in heaven,</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>may your name be kept holy.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  <JESUS>May your Kingdom come soon.</JESUS>  <JESUS>May your will
        be done on earth,</JESUS>  <JESUS>as it is in heaven.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  <JESUS>Give us today the food we need,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:11 '
        content: '  Or   <b>Give us today our food for the day; </b>  or   <b>Give
          us today our food for tomorrow.</b>    '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  <JESUS>and forgive us our sins,</JESUS>  <JESUS>as we have forgiven
        those who sin against us.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  <JESUS>And don\u2019t let us yield to temptation,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>but rescue us from the evil one.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:13a '
        content: '  Or   <b>And keep us from being tested.</b>    '
      - number: '6:13b '
        content: '  Or   <b>from evil. </b>  Some manuscripts add   <b>For yours
          is the kingdom and the power and the glory forever. Amen.</b>  '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CIf you forgive those who sin against you, your heavenly
        Father will forgive you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '<JESUS>But if you refuse to forgive others, your Father will not
        forgive your sins.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CAnd when you fast, don\u2019t make it obvious, as
        the hypocrites do, for they try to look miserable and disheveled so people
        will admire them for their fasting. I tell you the truth, that is the only
        reward they will ever get.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '<JESUS>But when you fast, comb your hair</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and
        wash your face.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:17 '
        content: Greek <b>anoint your head.</b>
    - name: '18: Teaching about Money and Possessions'
      title: Teaching about Money and Possessions
      number: 18
      content: '<JESUS>Then no one will notice that you are fasting, except your
        Father, who knows what you do in private. And your Father, who sees everything,
        will reward you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t store up treasures here on earth, where
        moths eat them and rust destroys them, and where thieves break in and steal.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '<JESUS>Store your treasures in heaven, where moths and rust cannot
        destroy, and thieves do not break in and steal.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '<JESUS>Wherever your treasure is, there the desires of your heart
        will also be.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CYour eye is like a lamp that provides light for your
        body. When your eye is healthy, your whole body is filled with light.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '<JESUS>But when your eye is unhealthy, your whole body is filled
        with darkness. And if the light you think you have is actually darkness,
        how deep that darkness is!</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CNo one can serve two masters. For you will hate one
        and love the other; you will be devoted to one and despise the other. You
        cannot serve God and be enslaved to money.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThat is why I tell you not to worry about everyday
        life\u2014whether you have enough food and drink, or enough clothes to wear.
        Isn\u2019t life more than food, and your body more than clothing?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>Look at the birds. They don\u2019t plant or harvest or store
        food in barns, for your heavenly Father feeds them. And aren\u2019t you far
        more valuable to him than they are?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '<JESUS>Can all your worries add a single moment to your life?</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CAnd why worry about your clothing? Look at the lilies
        of the field and how they grow. They don\u2019t work or make their clothing,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '<JESUS>yet Solomon in all his glory was not dressed as beautifully
        as they are.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '<JESUS>And if God cares so wonderfully for wildflowers that are here
        today and thrown into the fire tomorrow, he will certainly care for you.
        Why do you have so little faith?</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CSo don\u2019t worry about these things, saying, \u2018What
        will we eat? What will we drink? What will we wear?\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: '<JESUS>These things dominate the thoughts of unbelievers, but your
        heavenly Father already knows all your needs.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: '<JESUS>Seek the Kingdom of God</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>above
        all else, and live righteously, and he will give you everything you need.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:33 '
        content: Some manuscripts do not include <b>of God.</b>
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CSo don\u2019t worry about tomorrow, for tomorrow will
        bring its own worries. Today\u2019s trouble is enough for today.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Do Not Judge Others'
      title: Do Not Judge Others
      number: 1
      content: "    <JESUS>\u201CDo not judge others, and you will not be judged.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '<JESUS>For you will be treated as you treat others.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>The standard you use in judging is the standard by which you will
        be judged.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:2a '
        content: Or <b>For God will judge you as you judge others.</b>
      - number: '7:2b '
        content: 'Or <b>The measure you give will be the measure you get back.</b>  '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CAnd why worry about a speck in your friend\u2019s
        eye</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>when you have a log in your own?</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:3 '
        content: "  Greek   <b>your brother\u2019s eye; </b>  also in 7:5.  "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "<JESUS>How can you think of saying to your friend,</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>\u2018Let me help you get rid of that speck in your eye,\u2019 when
        you can\u2019t see past the log in your own eye?</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:4 '
        content: 'Greek <b>your brother.</b>  '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "<JESUS>Hypocrite! First get rid of the log in your own eye; then
        you will see well enough to deal with the speck in your friend\u2019s eye.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Effective Prayer'
      title: Effective Prayer
      number: 6
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t waste what is holy on people who are unholy.</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>Don\u2019t throw your pearls to pigs! They will trample
        the pearls, then turn and attack you.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:6 '
        content: "  Greek   <b>Don\u2019t give the sacred to dogs.</b>    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CKeep on asking, and you will receive what you ask
        for. Keep on seeking, and you will find. Keep on knocking, and the door will
        be opened to you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '<JESUS>For everyone who asks, receives. Everyone who seeks, finds.
        And to everyone who knocks, the door will be opened.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CYou parents\u2014if your children ask for a loaf of
        bread, do you give them a stone instead?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '<JESUS>Or if they ask for a fish, do you give them a snake? Of course
        not!</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Golden Rule'
      title: The Golden Rule
      number: 11
      content: '<JESUS>So if you sinful people know how to give good gifts to your
        children, how much more will your heavenly Father give good gifts to those
        who ask him.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Narrow Gate'
      title: The Narrow Gate
      number: 12
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CDo to others whatever you would like them to do to
        you. This is the essence of all that is taught in the law and the prophets.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CYou can enter God\u2019s Kingdom only through the
        narrow gate. The highway to hell</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>is broad,
        and its gate is wide for the many who choose that way.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:13 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>The road that leads to destruction.</b>  '
    - name: '14: The Tree and Its Fruit'
      title: The Tree and Its Fruit
      number: 14
      content: '<JESUS>But the gateway to life is very narrow and the road is difficult,
        and only a few ever find it.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBeware of false prophets who come disguised as harmless
        sheep but are really vicious wolves.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '<JESUS>You can identify them by their fruit, that is, by the way
        they act. Can you pick grapes from thornbushes, or figs from thistles?</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '<JESUS>A good tree produces good fruit, and a bad tree produces bad
        fruit.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>A good tree can\u2019t produce bad fruit, and a bad tree can\u2019t
        produce good fruit.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '<JESUS>So every tree that does not produce good fruit is chopped
        down and thrown into the fire.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: True Disciples'
      title: True Disciples
      number: 20
      content: '<JESUS>Yes, just as you can identify a tree by its fruit, so you
        can identify people by their actions.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CNot everyone who calls out to me, \u2018Lord! Lord!\u2019
        will enter the Kingdom of Heaven. Only those who actually do the will of
        my Father in heaven will enter.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "<JESUS>On judgment day many will say to me, \u2018Lord! Lord! We
        prophesied in your name and cast out demons in your name and performed many
        miracles in your name.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Building on a Solid Foundation'
      title: Building on a Solid Foundation
      number: 23
      content: "<JESUS>But I will reply, \u2018I never knew you. Get away from me,
        you who break God\u2019s laws.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CAnyone who listens to my teaching and follows it is
        wise, like a person who builds a house on solid rock.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "<JESUS>Though the rain comes in torrents and the floodwaters rise
        and the winds beat against that house, it won\u2019t collapse because it
        is built on bedrock.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>But anyone who hears my teaching and doesn\u2019t obey it
        is foolish, like a person who builds a house on sand.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "<JESUS>When the rains and floods come and the winds beat against
        that house, it will collapse with a mighty crash.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'When Jesus had finished saying these things, the crowds were amazed
        at his teaching, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "for he taught with real authority\u2014quite unlike their teachers
        of religious law."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Heals a Man with Leprosy'
      title: Jesus Heals a Man with Leprosy
      number: 1
      content: '  Large crowds followed Jesus as he came down the mountainside. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Suddenly, a man with leprosy approached him and knelt before him.
        \u201CLord,\u201D the man said, \u201Cif you are willing, you can heal me
        and make me clean.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Jesus reached out and touched him. <JESUS>\u201CI am willing,\u201D
        </JESUS>he said. <JESUS>\u201CBe healed!\u201D</JESUS> And instantly the
        leprosy disappeared. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: The Faith of a Roman Officer'
      title: The Faith of a Roman Officer
      number: 4
      content: "Then Jesus said to him, <JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t tell anyone about
        this. Instead, go to the priest and let him examine you. Take along the offering
        required in the law of Moses for those who have been healed of leprosy.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>This will be a public testimony that you have been cleansed.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:4 '
        content: See Lev 14:2-32.
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When Jesus returned to Capernaum, a Roman officer[[COMMENT(0)]] came
        and pleaded with him, '
      comments:
      - number: '8:5 '
        content: Greek <b>a centurion; </b>similarly in 8:8, 13.
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CLord, my young servant[[COMMENT(0)]] lies in bed, paralyzed
        and in terrible pain.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:6 '
        content: Or <b>child; </b>also in 8:13.
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CI will come and heal him.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But the officer said, \u201CLord, I am not worthy to have you come
        into my home. Just say the word from where you are, and my servant will be
        healed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "I know this because I am under the authority of my superior officers,
        and I have authority over my soldiers. I only need to say, \u2018Go,\u2019
        and they go, or \u2018Come,\u2019 and they come. And if I say to my slaves,
        \u2018Do this,\u2019 they do it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "When Jesus heard this, he was amazed. Turning to those who were following
        him, he said, <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth, I haven\u2019t seen faith
        like this in all Israel!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "<JESUS>And I tell you this, that many Gentiles will come from all
        over the world\u2014from east and west\u2014and sit down with Abraham, Isaac,
        and Jacob at the feast in the Kingdom of Heaven.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "<JESUS>But many Israelites\u2014those for whom the Kingdom was prepared\u2014will
        be thrown into outer darkness, where there will be weeping and gnashing of
        teeth.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Jesus Heals Many People'
      title: Jesus Heals Many People
      number: 13
      content: "Then Jesus said to the Roman officer, <JESUS>\u201CGo back home.
        Because you believed, it has happened.\u201D</JESUS> And the young servant
        was healed that same hour.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "When Jesus arrived at Peter\u2019s house, Peter\u2019s mother-in-law
        was sick in bed with a high fever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But when Jesus touched her hand, the fever left her. Then she got
        up and prepared a meal for him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'That evening many demon-possessed people were brought to Jesus. He
        cast out the evil spirits with a simple command, and he healed all the sick. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: The Cost of Following Jesus'
      title: The Cost of Following Jesus
      number: 17
      content: "This fulfilled the word of the Lord through the prophet Isaiah, who
        said,\u201CHe took our sicknessesand removed our diseases.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:17 '
        content: Isa 53:4.
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When Jesus saw the crowd around him, he instructed his disciples
        to cross to the other side of the lake.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then one of the teachers of religious law said to him, \u201CTeacher,
        I will follow you wherever you go.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CFoxes have dens to live in, and birds
        have nests, but the Son of Man</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>has no place
        even to lay his head.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:20 '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Another of his disciples said, \u201CLord, first let me return home
        and bury my father.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Jesus Calms the Storm'
      title: Jesus Calms the Storm
      number: 22
      content: "But Jesus told him, <JESUS>\u201CFollow me now. Let the spiritually
        dead bury their own dead.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:22 '
        content: Greek <b>Let the dead bury their own dead.</b>
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then Jesus got into the boat and started across the lake with his
        disciples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Suddenly, a fierce storm struck the lake, with waves breaking into
        the boat. But Jesus was sleeping. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The disciples went and woke him up, shouting, \u201CLord, save us!
        We\u2019re going to drown!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CWhy are you afraid? You have so little
        faith!\u201D</JESUS> Then he got up and rebuked the wind and waves, and suddenly
        there was a great calm.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Jesus Heals Two Demon-Possessed Men'
      title: Jesus Heals Two Demon-Possessed Men
      number: 27
      content: "The disciples were amazed. \u201CWho is this man?\u201D they asked.
        \u201CEven the winds and waves obey him!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'When Jesus arrived on the other side of the lake, in the region of
        the Gadarenes,[[COMMENT(0)]] two men who were possessed by demons met him.
        They came out of the tombs and were so violent that no one could go through
        that area.  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:28 '
        content: Other manuscripts read <b>Gerasenes; </b>still others read <b>Gergesenes.
          </b>Compare Mark 5:1; Luke 8:26.
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "They began screaming at him, \u201CWhy are you interfering with us,
        Son of God? Have you come here to torture us before God\u2019s appointed
        time?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'There happened to be a large herd of pigs feeding in the distance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "So the demons begged, \u201CIf you cast us out, send us into that
        herd of pigs.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CAll right, go!\u201D </JESUS>Jesus commanded them.
        So the demons came out of the men and entered the pigs, and the whole herd
        plunged down the steep hillside into the lake and drowned in the water.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The herdsmen fled to the nearby town, telling everyone what happened
        to the demon-possessed men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: Then the entire town came out to meet Jesus, but they begged him to
        go away and leave them alone.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Heals a Paralyzed Man'
      title: Jesus Heals a Paralyzed Man
      number: 1
      content: '  Jesus climbed into a boat and went back across the lake to his
        own town. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Some people brought to him a paralyzed man on a mat. Seeing their
        faith, Jesus said to the paralyzed man, <JESUS>\u201CBe encouraged, my child!
        Your sins are forgiven.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But some of the teachers of religious law said to themselves, \u201CThat\u2019s
        blasphemy! Does he think he\u2019s God?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Jesus knew[[COMMENT(0)]] what they were thinking, so he asked them,
        <JESUS>\u201CWhy do you have such evil thoughts in your hearts?</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:4 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>saw.</b>
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "<JESUS>Is it easier to say \u2018Your sins are forgiven,\u2019 or
        \u2018Stand up and walk\u2019?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "<JESUS>So I will prove to you that the Son of Man</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>has the authority on earth to forgive sins.\u201D</JESUS> Then Jesus
        turned to the paralyzed man and said, <JESUS>\u201CStand up, pick up your
        mat, and go home!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:6 '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the man jumped up and went home! '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Jesus Calls Matthew'
      title: Jesus Calls Matthew
      number: 8
      content: 'Fear swept through the crowd as they saw this happen. And they praised
        God for giving humans such authority.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "As Jesus was walking along, he saw a man named Matthew sitting at
        his tax collector\u2019s booth. <JESUS>\u201CFollow me and be my disciple,\u201D
        </JESUS>Jesus said to him. So Matthew got up and followed him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Later, Matthew invited Jesus and his disciples to his home as dinner
        guests, along with many tax collectors and other disreputable sinners. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But when the Pharisees saw this, they asked his disciples, \u201CWhy
        does your teacher eat with such scum?[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:11 '
        content: Greek <b>with tax collectors and sinners?</b>
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "When Jesus heard this, he said, <JESUS>\u201CHealthy people don\u2019t
        need a doctor\u2014sick people do.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: A Discussion about Fasting'
      title: A Discussion about Fasting
      number: 13
      content: "Then he added, <JESUS>\u201CNow go and learn the meaning of this
        Scripture: \u2018I want you to show mercy, not offer sacrifices.\u2019</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>For I have come to call not those who think they are righteous, but
        those who know they are sinners.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:13 '
        content: Hos 6:6 (Greek version).
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "One day the disciples of John the Baptist came to Jesus and asked
        him, \u201CWhy don\u2019t your disciples fast[[COMMENT(0)]] like we do and
        the Pharisees do?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:14 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>fast often.</b>
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CDo wedding guests mourn while celebrating
        with the groom? Of course not. But someday the groom will be taken away from
        them, and then they will fast.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBesides, who would patch old clothing with new cloth?
        For the new patch would shrink and rip away from the old cloth, leaving an
        even bigger tear than before.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Jesus Heals in Response to Faith'
      title: Jesus Heals in Response to Faith
      number: 17
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CAnd no one puts new wine into old wineskins. For the
        old skins would burst from the pressure, spilling the wine and ruining the
        skins. New wine is stored in new wineskins so that both are preserved.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "As Jesus was saying this, the leader of a synagogue came and knelt
        before him. \u201CMy daughter has just died,\u201D he said, \u201Cbut you
        can bring her back to life again if you just come and lay your hand on her.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So Jesus and his disciples got up and went with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Just then a woman who had suffered for twelve years with constant
        bleeding came up behind him. She touched the fringe of his robe, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "for she thought, \u201CIf I can just touch his robe, I will be healed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Jesus turned around, and when he saw her he said, <JESUS>\u201CDaughter,
        be encouraged! Your faith has made you well.\u201D</JESUS> And the woman
        was healed at that moment.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "When Jesus arrived at the official\u2019s home, he saw the noisy
        crowd and heard the funeral music. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CGet out!\u201D </JESUS>he told them. <JESUS>\u201CThe
        girl isn\u2019t dead; she\u2019s only asleep.\u201D</JESUS> But the crowd
        laughed at him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'After the crowd was put outside, however, Jesus went in and took
        the girl by the hand, and she stood up! '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Jesus Heals the Blind'
      title: Jesus Heals the Blind
      number: 26
      content: 'The report of this miracle swept through the entire countryside.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "After Jesus left the girl\u2019s home, two blind men followed along
        behind him, shouting, \u201CSon of David, have mercy on us!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "They went right into the house where he was staying, and Jesus asked
        them, <JESUS>\u201CDo you believe I can make you see?\u201D</JESUS>\u201CYes,
        Lord,\u201D they told him, \u201Cwe do.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then he touched their eyes and said, <JESUS>\u201CBecause of your
        faith, it will happen.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then their eyes were opened, and they could see! Jesus sternly warned
        them, <JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t tell anyone about this.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'But instead, they went out and spread his fame all over the region.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "When they left, a demon-possessed man who couldn\u2019t speak was
        brought to Jesus. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "So Jesus cast out the demon, and then the man began to speak. The
        crowds were amazed. \u201CNothing like this has ever happened in Israel!\u201D
        they exclaimed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: The Need for Workers'
      title: The Need for Workers
      number: 34
      content: "But the Pharisees said, \u201CHe can cast out demons because he is
        empowered by the prince of demons.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Jesus traveled through all the towns and villages of that area, teaching
        in the synagogues and announcing the Good News about the Kingdom. And he
        healed every kind of disease and illness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'When he saw the crowds, he had compassion on them because they were
        confused and helpless, like sheep without a shepherd. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "He said to his disciples, <JESUS>\u201CThe harvest is great, but
        the workers are few.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "<JESUS>So pray to the Lord who is in charge of the harvest; ask him
        to send more workers into his fields.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Sends Out the Twelve Apostles'
      title: Jesus Sends Out the Twelve Apostles
      number: 1
      content: '  Jesus called his twelve disciples together and gave them authority
        to cast out evil[[COMMENT(0)]] spirits and to heal every kind of disease
        and illness. '
      comments:
      - number: '10:1 '
        content: Greek <b>unclean.</b>
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Here are the names of the twelve apostles:first, Simon (also called
        Peter),then Andrew (Peter\u2019s brother),James (son of Zebedee),John (James\u2019s
        brother),  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Philip,Bartholomew,Thomas,Matthew (the tax collector),James (son
        of Alphaeus),Thaddaeus,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:3 '
        content: Other manuscripts read <b>Lebbaeus; </b>still others read <b>Lebbaeus
          who is called Thaddaeus.</b>
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Simon (the zealot[[COMMENT(0)]]),Judas Iscariot (who later betrayed
        him).  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:4 '
        content: Greek <b>the Cananean, </b>an Aramaic term for Jewish nationalists.
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Jesus sent out the twelve apostles with these instructions: <JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t
        go to the Gentiles or the Samaritans,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "<JESUS>but only to the people of Israel\u2014God\u2019s lost sheep.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '<JESUS>Go and announce to them that the Kingdom of Heaven is near.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:7 '
        content: Or <b>has come, </b>or <b>is coming soon.</b>
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '<JESUS>Heal the sick, raise the dead, cure those with leprosy, and
        cast out demons. Give as freely as you have received!</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t take any money in your money belts\u2014no
        gold, silver, or even copper coins.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>Don\u2019t carry a traveler\u2019s bag with a change of clothes
        and sandals or even a walking stick. Don\u2019t hesitate to accept hospitality,
        because those who work deserve to be fed.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CWhenever you enter a city or village, search for a
        worthy person and stay in his home until you leave town.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '<JESUS>When you enter the home, give it your blessing.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '<JESUS>If it turns out to be a worthy home, let your blessing stand;
        if it is not, take back the blessing.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '<JESUS>If any household or town refuses to welcome you or listen
        to your message, shake its dust from your feet as you leave.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '<JESUS>I tell you the truth, the wicked cities of Sodom and Gomorrah
        will be better off than such a town on the judgment day.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CLook, I am sending you out as sheep among wolves.
        So be as shrewd as snakes and harmless as doves.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '<JESUS>But beware! For you will be handed over to the courts and
        will be flogged with whips in the synagogues.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '<JESUS>You will stand trial before governors and kings because you
        are my followers. But this will be your opportunity to tell the rulers and
        other unbelievers about me.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:18 '
        content: Or <b>But this will be your testimony against the rulers and other
          unbelievers.</b>
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>When you are arrested, don\u2019t worry about how to respond
        or what to say. God will give you the right words at the right time.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>For it is not you who will be speaking\u2014it will be the
        Spirit of your Father speaking through you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CA brother will betray his brother to death, a father
        will betray his own child, and children will rebel against their parents
        and cause them to be killed.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '<JESUS>And all nations will hate you because you are my followers.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>But everyone who endures to the end will be saved.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:22 '
        content: Greek <b>on account of my name.</b>
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '<JESUS>When you are persecuted in one town, flee to the next. I tell
        you the truth, the Son of Man</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>will return before
        you have reached all the towns of Israel.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:23 '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself.  "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CStudents</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>are not greater
        than their teacher, and slaves are not greater than their master.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:24 '
        content: '  Or   <b>Disciples.</b>  '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '<JESUS>Students are to be like their teacher, and slaves are to be
        like their master. And since I, the master of the household, have been called
        the prince of demons,</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>the members of my household
        will be called by even worse names!</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:25 '
        content: 'Greek <b>Beelzeboul; </b>other manuscripts read <b>Beezeboul; </b>Latin
          version reads <b>Beelzebub.</b>  '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBut don\u2019t be afraid of those who threaten you.
        For the time is coming when everything that is covered will be revealed,
        and all that is secret will be made known to all.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '<JESUS>What I tell you now in the darkness, shout abroad when daybreak
        comes. What I whisper in your ear, shout from the housetops for all to hear!</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t be afraid of those who want to kill your
        body; they cannot touch your soul. Fear only God, who can destroy both soul
        and body in hell.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:28 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>Gehenna.</b>  '
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "<JESUS>What is the price of two sparrows\u2014one copper coin</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>?
        But not a single sparrow can fall to the ground without your Father knowing
        it.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:29 '
        content: "Greek <b>one assarion </b>[i.e., one \u201Cas,\u201D a Roman coin
          equal to 1/16 of a denarius].  "
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '<JESUS>And the very hairs on your head are all numbered.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "<JESUS>So don\u2019t be afraid; you are more valuable to God than
        a whole flock of sparrows.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CEveryone who acknowledges me publicly here on earth,
        I will also acknowledge before my Father in heaven.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: '<JESUS>But everyone who denies me here on earth, I will also deny
        before my Father in heaven.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t imagine that I came to bring peace to the
        earth! I came not to bring peace, but a sword.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "  <JESUS>\u2018I have come to set a man against his father,</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>a daughter against her mother,</JESUS>  <JESUS>and a daughter-in-law
        against her mother-in-law.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "  <JESUS>Your enemies will be right in your own household!\u2019</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:35-36 '
        content: '  Mic 7:6.  '
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CIf you love your father or mother more than you love
        me, you are not worthy of being mine; or if you love your son or daughter
        more than me, you are not worthy of being mine.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: '<JESUS>If you refuse to take up your cross and follow me, you are
        not worthy of being mine.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: '<JESUS>If you cling to your life, you will lose it; but if you give
        up your life for me, you will find it.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CAnyone who receives you receives me, and anyone who
        receives me receives the Father who sent me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: '<JESUS>If you receive a prophet as one who speaks for God,</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>you will be given the same reward as a prophet. And if you receive
        righteous people because of their righteousness, you will be given a reward
        like theirs.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:41 '
        content: Greek <b>receive a prophet in the name of a prophet.</b>
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "<JESUS>And if you give even a cup of cold water to one of the least
        of my followers, you will surely be rewarded.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus and John the Baptist'
      title: Jesus and John the Baptist
      number: 1
      content: '  When Jesus had finished giving these instructions to his twelve
        disciples, he went out to teach and preach in towns throughout the region.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'John the Baptist, who was in prison, heard about all the things the
        Messiah was doing. So he sent his disciples to ask Jesus, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CAre you the Messiah we\u2019ve been expecting,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        or should we keep looking for someone else?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:3 '
        content: Greek <b>Are you the one who is coming?</b>
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Jesus told them, <JESUS>\u201CGo back to John and tell him what you
        have heard and seen\u2014</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "<JESUS>the blind see, the lame walk, those with leprosy are cured,
        the deaf hear, the dead are raised to life, and the Good News is being preached
        to the poor.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "<JESUS>And he added, \u201CGod blesses those who do not fall away
        because of me.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:6 '
        content: 'Or <b>who are not offended by me.</b>  '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "As John\u2019s disciples were leaving, Jesus began talking about
        him to the crowds. <JESUS>\u201CWhat kind of man did you go into the wilderness
        to see? Was he a weak reed, swayed by every breath of wind?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '<JESUS>Or were you expecting to see a man dressed in expensive clothes?
        No, people with expensive clothes live in palaces.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '<JESUS>Were you looking for a prophet? Yes, and he is more than a
        prophet.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>John is the man to whom the Scriptures refer when they say,</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>\u2018Look, I am sending my messenger ahead of you,</JESUS>  <JESUS>and
        he will prepare your way before you.\u2019</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:10 '
        content: '  Mal 3:1.  '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth, of all who have ever lived,
        none is greater than John the Baptist. Yet even the least person in the Kingdom
        of Heaven is greater than he is!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '<JESUS>And from the time John the Baptist began preaching until now,
        the Kingdom of Heaven has been forcefully advancing,</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>and violent people are attacking it.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:12 '
        content: Or <b>the Kingdom of Heaven has suffered from violence.</b>
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '<JESUS>For before John came, all the prophets and the law of Moses
        looked forward to this present time.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '<JESUS>And if you are willing to accept what I say, he is Elijah,
        the one the prophets said would come.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:14 '
        content: See Mal 4:5.
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '<JESUS>Anyone with ears to hear should listen and understand!</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CTo what can I compare this generation? It is like
        children playing a game in the public square. They complain to their friends,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  <JESUS>\u2018We played wedding songs,</JESUS>  <JESUS>and you didn\u2019t
        dance,</JESUS>  <JESUS>so we played funeral songs,</JESUS>  <JESUS>and you
        didn\u2019t mourn.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  <JESUS>For John didn\u2019t spend his time eating and drinking,
        and you say, \u2018He\u2019s possessed by a demon.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Judgment for the Unbelievers'
      title: Judgment for the Unbelievers
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>The Son of Man,</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>on the other
        hand, feasts and drinks, and you say, \u2018He\u2019s a glutton and a drunkard,
        and a friend of tax collectors and other sinners!\u2019 But wisdom is shown
        to be right by its results.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:19 '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself.  "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Jesus began to denounce the towns where he had done so many
        of his miracles, because they hadn\u2019t repented of their sins and turned
        to God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CWhat sorrow awaits you, Korazin and Bethsaida! For if
        the miracles I did in you had been done in wicked Tyre and Sidon, their people
        would have repented of their sins long ago, clothing themselves in burlap
        and throwing ashes on their heads to show their remorse.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '<JESUS>I tell you, Tyre and Sidon will be better off on judgment
        day than you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CAnd you people of Capernaum, will you be honored in
        heaven? No, you will go down to the place of the dead.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>For if the miracles I did for you had been done in wicked Sodom, it
        would still be here today.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:23 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>to Hades.</b>  '
    - name: "24: Jesus\u2019 Prayer of Thanksgiving"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 Prayer of Thanksgiving"
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>I tell you, even Sodom will be better off on judgment day
        than you.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "At that time Jesus prayed this prayer: <JESUS>\u201CO Father, Lord
        of heaven and earth, thank you for hiding these things from those who think
        themselves wise and clever, and for revealing them to the childlike.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '<JESUS>Yes, Father, it pleased you to do it this way!</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CMy Father has entrusted everything to me. No one truly
        knows the Son except the Father, and no one truly knows the Father except
        the Son and those to whom the Son chooses to reveal him.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CCome to me, all of you who are weary
        and carry heavy burdens, and I will give you rest.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '<JESUS>Take my yoke upon you. Let me teach you, because I am humble
        and gentle at heart, and you will find rest for your souls.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "<JESUS>For my yoke is easy to bear, and the burden I give you is
        light.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Discussion about the Sabbath'
      title: A Discussion about the Sabbath
      number: 1
      content: '  At about that time Jesus was walking through some grainfields on
        the Sabbath. His disciples were hungry, so they began breaking off some heads
        of grain and eating them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "But some Pharisees saw them do it and protested, \u201CLook, your
        disciples are breaking the law by harvesting grain on the Sabbath.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CHaven\u2019t you read in the Scriptures
        what David did when he and his companions were hungry?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '<JESUS>He went into the house of God, and he and his companions broke
        the law by eating the sacred loaves of bread that only the priests are allowed
        to eat.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "<JESUS>And haven\u2019t you read in the law of Moses that the priests
        on duty in the Temple may work on the Sabbath?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '<JESUS>I tell you, there is one here who is even greater than the
        Temple!</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "<JESUS>But you would not have condemned my innocent disciples if
        you knew the meaning of this Scripture: \u2018I want you to show mercy, not
        offer sacrifices.\u2019</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:7 '
        content: Hos 6:6 (Greek version).
    - name: '8: Jesus Heals on the Sabbath'
      title: Jesus Heals on the Sabbath
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>For the Son of Man</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>is Lord,
        even over the Sabbath!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:8 '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Jesus went over to their synagogue, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "where he noticed a man with a deformed hand. The Pharisees asked
        Jesus, \u201CDoes the law permit a person to work by healing on the Sabbath?\u201D
        (They were hoping he would say yes, so they could bring charges against him.)  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And he answered, <JESUS>\u201CIf you had a sheep that fell into a
        well on the Sabbath, wouldn\u2019t you work to pull it out? Of course you
        would.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "<JESUS>And how much more valuable is a person than a sheep! Yes,
        the law permits a person to do good on the Sabbath.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then he said to the man, <JESUS>\u201CHold out your hand.\u201D</JESUS>
        So the man held out his hand, and it was restored, just like the other one! "
      comments: []
    - name: "14: Jesus, God\u2019s Chosen Servant"
      title: "Jesus, God\u2019s Chosen Servant"
      number: 14
      content: 'Then the Pharisees called a meeting to plot how to kill Jesus.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But Jesus knew what they were planning. So he left that area, and
        many people followed him. He healed all the sick among them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'but he warned them not to reveal who he was. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'This fulfilled the prophecy of Isaiah concerning him:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CLook at my Servant, whom I have chosen.He is my Beloved, who
        pleases me.I will put my Spirit upon him,and he will proclaim justice to
        the nations.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He will not fight or shoutor raise his voice in public.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'He will not crush the weakest reedor put out a flickering candle.Finally
        he will cause justice to be victorious.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Jesus and the Prince of Demons'
      title: Jesus and the Prince of Demons
      number: 21
      content: "And his name will be the hopeof all the world.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:18-21 '
        content: Isa 42:1-4 (Greek version for 42:4).
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then a demon-possessed man, who was blind and couldn\u2019t speak,
        was brought to Jesus. He healed the man so that he could both speak and see. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The crowd was amazed and asked, \u201CCould it be that Jesus is the
        Son of David, the Messiah?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "But when the Pharisees heard about the miracle, they said, \u201CNo
        wonder he can cast out demons. He gets his power from Satan,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the prince of demons.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:24 '
        content: Greek <b>Beelzeboul; </b>also in 12:27. Other manuscripts read <b>Beezeboul;
          </b>Latin version reads <b>Beelzebub.</b>
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Jesus knew their thoughts and replied, <JESUS>\u201CAny kingdom divided
        by civil war is doomed. A town or family splintered by feuding will fall
        apart.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '<JESUS>And if Satan is casting out Satan, he is divided and fighting
        against himself. His own kingdom will not survive.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '<JESUS>And if I am empowered by Satan, what about your own exorcists?
        They cast out demons, too, so they will condemn you for what you have said.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '<JESUS>But if I am casting out demons by the Spirit of God, then
        the Kingdom of God has arrived among you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "<JESUS>For who is powerful enough to enter the house of a strong
        man and plunder his goods? Only someone even stronger\u2014someone who could
        tie him up and then plunder his house.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CAnyone who isn\u2019t with me opposes me, and anyone
        who isn\u2019t working with me is actually working against me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CSo I tell you, every sin and blasphemy can be forgiven\u2014except
        blasphemy against the Holy Spirit, which will never be forgiven.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: '<JESUS>Anyone who speaks against the Son of Man can be forgiven,
        but anyone who speaks against the Holy Spirit will never be forgiven, either
        in this world or in the world to come.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CA tree is identified by its fruit. If a tree is good,
        its fruit will be good. If a tree is bad, its fruit will be bad.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: '<JESUS>You brood of snakes! How could evil men like you speak what
        is good and right? For whatever is in your heart determines what you say.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: '<JESUS>A good person produces good things from the treasury of a
        good heart, and an evil person produces evil things from the treasury of
        an evil heart.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: '<JESUS>And I tell you this, you must give an account on judgment
        day for every idle word you speak.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: The Sign of Jonah'
      title: The Sign of Jonah
      number: 37
      content: "<JESUS>The words you say will either acquit you or condemn you.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "One day some teachers of religious law and Pharisees came to Jesus
        and said, \u201CTeacher, we want you to show us a miraculous sign to prove
        your authority.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "But Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201COnly an evil, adulterous generation
        would demand a miraculous sign; but the only sign I will give them is the
        sign of the prophet Jonah.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: '<JESUS>For as Jonah was in the belly of the great fish for three
        days and three nights, so will the Son of Man be in the heart of the earth
        for three days and three nights.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThe people of Nineveh will stand up against this generation
        on judgment day and condemn it, for they repented of their sins at the preaching
        of Jonah. Now someone greater than Jonah is here\u2014but you refuse to repent.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "<JESUS>The queen of Sheba</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>will also
        stand up against this generation on judgment day and condemn it, for she
        came from a distant land to hear the wisdom of Solomon. Now someone greater
        than Solomon is here\u2014but you refuse to listen.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:42 '
        content: 'Greek <b>The queen of the south.</b>  '
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CWhen an evil</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>spirit
        leaves a person, it goes into the desert, seeking rest but finding none.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:43 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>unclean.</b>  '
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "<JESUS>Then it says, \u2018I will return to the person I came from.\u2019
        So it returns and finds its former home empty, swept, and in order.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: The True Family of Jesus'
      title: The True Family of Jesus
      number: 45
      content: "<JESUS>Then the spirit finds seven other spirits more evil than itself,
        and they all enter the person and live there. And so that person is worse
        off than before. That will be the experience of this evil generation.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'As Jesus was speaking to the crowd, his mother and brothers stood
        outside, asking to speak to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "Someone told Jesus, \u201CYour mother and your brothers are standing
        outside, and they want to speak to you.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:47 '
        content: Some manuscripts do not include verse 47. Compare Mark 3:32 and
          Luke 8:20.
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "Jesus asked, <JESUS>\u201CWho is my mother? Who are my brothers?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "Then he pointed to his disciples and said, <JESUS>\u201CLook, these
        are my mother and brothers.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "<JESUS>Anyone who does the will of my Father in heaven is my brother
        and sister and mother!\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Parable of the Farmer Scattering Seed'
      title: Parable of the Farmer Scattering Seed
      number: 1
      content: '  Later that same day Jesus left the house and sat beside the lake. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'A large crowd soon gathered around him, so he got into a boat. Then
        he sat there and taught as the people stood on the shore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "He told many stories in the form of parables, such as this one: 
        <JESUS>\u201CListen! A farmer went out to plant some seeds.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '<JESUS>As he scattered them across his field, some seeds fell on
        a footpath, and the birds came and ate them.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '<JESUS>Other seeds fell on shallow soil with underlying rock. The
        seeds sprouted quickly because the soil was shallow.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "<JESUS>But the plants soon wilted under the hot sun, and since they
        didn\u2019t have deep roots, they died.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '<JESUS>Other seeds fell among thorns that grew up and choked out
        the tender plants.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '<JESUS>Still other seeds fell on fertile soil, and they produced
        a crop that was thirty, sixty, and even a hundred times as much as had been
        planted!</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "<JESUS>Anyone with ears to hear should listen and understand.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "His disciples came and asked him, \u201CWhy do you use parables when
        you talk to the people?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "He replied, <JESUS>\u201CYou are permitted to understand the secrets</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>of the Kingdom of Heaven, but others are not.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:11 '
        content: 'Greek <b>the mysteries.</b>  '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '<JESUS>To those who listen to my teaching, more understanding will
        be given, and they will have an abundance of knowledge. But for those who
        are not listening, even what little understanding they have will be taken
        away from them.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "<JESUS>That is why I use these parables,</JESUS>  <JESUS>For they
        look, but they don\u2019t really see.</JESUS>  <JESUS>They hear, but they
        don\u2019t really listen or understand.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "  <JESUS>This fulfills the prophecy of Isaiah that says,</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>\u2018When you hear what I say,</JESUS>  <JESUS>you will not understand.</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>When you see what I do,</JESUS>  <JESUS>you will not comprehend.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "  <JESUS>For the hearts of these people are hardened,</JESUS>  <JESUS>and
        their ears cannot hear,</JESUS>  <JESUS>and they have closed their eyes\u2014</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>so their eyes cannot see,</JESUS>  <JESUS>and their ears cannot hear,</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>and their hearts cannot understand,</JESUS>  <JESUS>and they cannot
        turn to me</JESUS>  <JESUS>and let me heal them.\u2019</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:14-15 '
        content: '  Isa 6:9-10 (Greek version).  '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBut blessed are your eyes, because they see; and your
        ears, because they hear.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "<JESUS>I tell you the truth, many prophets and righteous people longed
        to see what you see, but they didn\u2019t see it. And they longed to hear
        what you hear, but they didn\u2019t hear it.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CNow listen to the explanation of the parable about
        the farmer planting seeds:</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>The seed that fell on the footpath represents those who hear
        the message about the Kingdom and don\u2019t understand it. Then the evil
        one comes and snatches away the seed that was planted in their hearts.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '<JESUS>The seed on the rocky soil represents those who hear the message
        and immediately receive it with joy.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>But since they don\u2019t have deep roots, they don\u2019t
        last long. They fall away as soon as they have problems or are persecuted
        for believing God\u2019s word.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "<JESUS>The seed that fell among the thorns represents those who hear
        God\u2019s word, but all too quickly the message is crowded out by the worries
        of this life and the lure of wealth, so no fruit is produced.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Parable of the Wheat and Weeds'
      title: Parable of the Wheat and Weeds
      number: 23
      content: "<JESUS>The seed that fell on good soil represents those who truly
        hear and understand God\u2019s word and produce a harvest of thirty, sixty,
        or even a hundred times as much as had been planted!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Here is another story Jesus told: <JESUS>\u201CThe Kingdom of Heaven
        is like a farmer who planted good seed in his field.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '<JESUS>But that night as the workers slept, his enemy came and planted
        weeds among the wheat, then slipped away.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '<JESUS>When the crop began to grow and produce grain, the weeds also
        grew.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThe farmer\u2019s workers went to him and said, \u2018Sir,
        the field where you planted that good seed is full of weeds! Where did they
        come from?\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201C\u2018An enemy has done this!\u2019 the farmer exclaimed.</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>\u201C\u2018Should we pull out the weeds?\u2019 they asked.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201C\u2018No,\u2019 he replied, \u2018you\u2019ll uproot
        the wheat if you do.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: Parable of the Mustard Seed'
      title: Parable of the Mustard Seed
      number: 30
      content: "<JESUS>Let both grow together until the harvest. Then I will tell
        the harvesters to sort out the weeds, tie them into bundles, and burn them,
        and to put the wheat in the barn.\u2019\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Here is another illustration Jesus used: <JESUS>\u201CThe Kingdom
        of Heaven is like a mustard seed planted in a field.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: Parable of the Yeast'
      title: Parable of the Yeast
      number: 32
      content: "<JESUS>It is the smallest of all seeds, but it becomes the largest
        of garden plants; it grows into a tree, and birds come and make nests in
        its branches.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Jesus also used this illustration: <JESUS>\u201CThe Kingdom of Heaven
        is like the yeast a woman used in making bread. Even though she put only
        a little yeast in three measures of flour, it permeated every part of the
        dough.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Jesus always used stories and illustrations like these when speaking
        to the crowds. In fact, he never spoke to them without using such parables. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: Parable of the Wheat and Weeds Explained'
      title: Parable of the Wheat and Weeds Explained
      number: 35
      content: "This fulfilled what God had spoken through the prophet:\u201CI will
        speak to you in parables.I will explain things hidden since the creation
        of the world.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:35 '
        content: Some manuscripts do not include <b>of the world. </b>Ps 78:2.
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then, leaving the crowds outside, Jesus went into the house. His
        disciples said, \u201CPlease explain to us the story of the weeds in the
        field.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CThe Son of Man</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>is the farmer who plants the good seed.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:37 '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: '<JESUS>The field is the world, and the good seed represents the people
        of the Kingdom. The weeds are the people who belong to the evil one.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: '<JESUS>The enemy who planted the weeds among the wheat is the devil.
        The harvest is the end of the world,</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and the
        harvesters are the angels.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:39 '
        content: Or <b>the age; </b>also in 13:40, 49.
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CJust as the weeds are sorted out and burned in the
        fire, so it will be at the end of the world.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: '<JESUS>The Son of Man will send his angels, and they will remove
        from his Kingdom everything that causes sin and all who do evil.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: '<JESUS>And the angels will throw them into the fiery furnace, where
        there will be weeping and gnashing of teeth.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: Parables of the Hidden Treasure and the Pearl'
      title: Parables of the Hidden Treasure and the Pearl
      number: 43
      content: "<JESUS>Then the righteous will shine like the sun in their Father\u2019s
        Kingdom. Anyone with ears to hear should listen and understand!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThe Kingdom of Heaven is like a treasure that a man
        discovered hidden in a field. In his excitement, he hid it again and sold
        everything he owned to get enough money to buy the field.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CAgain, the Kingdom of Heaven is like a merchant on
        the lookout for choice pearls.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: Parable of the Fishing Net'
      title: Parable of the Fishing Net
      number: 46
      content: '<JESUS>When he discovered a pearl of great value, he sold everything
        he owned and bought it!</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CAgain, the Kingdom of Heaven is like a fishing net
        that was thrown into the water and caught fish of every kind.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: '<JESUS>When the net was full, they dragged it up onto the shore,
        sat down, and sorted the good fish into crates, but threw the bad ones away.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: '<JESUS>That is the way it will be at the end of the world. The angels
        will come and separate the wicked people from the righteous,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: '<JESUS>throwing the wicked into the fiery furnace, where there will
        be weeping and gnashing of teeth.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "<JESUS>Do you understand all these things?\u201D</JESUS>\u201CYes,\u201D
        they said, \u201Cwe do.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: Jesus Rejected at Nazareth'
      title: Jesus Rejected at Nazareth
      number: 52
      content: "Then he added, <JESUS>\u201CEvery teacher of religious law who becomes
        a disciple in the Kingdom of Heaven is like a homeowner who brings from his
        storeroom new gems of truth as well as old.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'When Jesus had finished telling these stories and illustrations,
        he left that part of the country. '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "He returned to Nazareth, his hometown. When he taught there in the
        synagogue, everyone was amazed and said, \u201CWhere does he get this wisdom
        and the power to do miracles?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: "Then they scoffed, \u201CHe\u2019s just the carpenter\u2019s son,
        and we know Mary, his mother, and his brothers\u2014James, Joseph,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Simon, and Judas. "
      comments:
      - number: '13:55 '
        content: Other manuscripts read <b>Joses; </b>still others read <b>John.</b>
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "All his sisters live right here among us. Where did he learn all
        these things?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "And they were deeply offended and refused to believe in him.Then
        Jesus told them, <JESUS>\u201CA prophet is honored everywhere except in his
        own hometown and among his own family.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: And so he did only a few miracles there because of their unbelief.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Death of John the Baptist'
      title: The Death of John the Baptist
      number: 1
      content: '  When Herod Antipas, the ruler of Galilee,[[COMMENT(0)]] heard about
        Jesus, '
      comments:
      - number: '14:1 '
        content: Greek <b>Herod the tetrarch. </b>Herod Antipas was a son of King
          Herod and was ruler over Galilee.
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "he said to his advisers, \u201CThis must be John the Baptist raised
        from the dead! That is why he can do such miracles.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For Herod had arrested and imprisoned John as a favor to his wife
        Herodias (the former wife of Herod\u2019s brother Philip). "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "John had been telling Herod, \u201CIt is against God\u2019s law for
        you to marry her.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Herod wanted to kill John, but he was afraid of a riot, because all
        the people believed John was a prophet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But at a birthday party for Herod, Herodias\u2019s daughter performed
        a dance that greatly pleased him, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'so he promised with a vow to give her anything she wanted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "At her mother\u2019s urging, the girl said, \u201CI want the head
        of John the Baptist on a tray!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then the king regretted what he had said; but because of the vow
        he had made in front of his guests, he issued the necessary orders. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So John was beheaded in the prison, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and his head was brought on a tray and given to the girl, who took
        it to her mother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Jesus Feeds Five Thousand'
      title: Jesus Feeds Five Thousand
      number: 12
      content: "Later, John\u2019s disciples came for his body and buried it. Then
        they went and told Jesus what had happened.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'As soon as Jesus heard the news, he left in a boat to a remote area
        to be alone. But the crowds heard where he was headed and followed on foot
        from many towns. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Jesus saw the huge crowd as he stepped from the boat, and he had
        compassion on them and healed their sick.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "That evening the disciples came to him and said, \u201CThis is a
        remote place, and it\u2019s already getting late. Send the crowds away so
        they can go to the villages and buy food for themselves.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CThat isn\u2019t necessary\u2014you feed
        them.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CBut we have only five loaves of bread and two fish!\u201D they
        answered.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBring them here,\u201D </JESUS>he said. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then he told the people to sit down on the grass. Jesus took the
        five loaves and two fish, looked up toward heaven, and blessed them. Then,
        breaking the loaves into pieces, he gave the bread to the disciples, who
        distributed it to the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'They all ate as much as they wanted, and afterward, the disciples
        picked up twelve baskets of leftovers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Jesus Walks on Water'
      title: Jesus Walks on Water
      number: 21
      content: 'About 5,000 men were fed that day, in addition to all the women and
        children!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Immediately after this, Jesus insisted that his disciples get back
        into the boat and cross to the other side of the lake, while he sent the
        people home. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'After sending them home, he went up into the hills by himself to
        pray. Night fell while he was there alone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Meanwhile, the disciples were in trouble far away from land, for
        a strong wind had risen, and they were fighting heavy waves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "About three o\u2019clock in the morning[[COMMENT(0)]] Jesus came
        toward them, walking on the water. "
      comments:
      - number: '14:25 '
        content: Greek <b>In the fourth watch of the night.</b>
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "When the disciples saw him walking on the water, they were terrified.
        In their fear, they cried out, \u201CIt\u2019s a ghost!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But Jesus spoke to them at once. <JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t be afraid,\u201D
        </JESUS>he said. <JESUS>\u201CTake courage. I am here!</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>Greek
        reads </smallcaps><JESUS>\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:27 '
        content: "Or <b>The \u2018<span class=\"ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf\">I Am</span>\u2019
          is here; </b><b>I am. </b>See Exod 3:14."
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then Peter called to him, \u201CLord, if it\u2019s really you, tell
        me to come to you, walking on the water.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CYes, come,\u201D </JESUS>Jesus said.So Peter went
        over the side of the boat and walked on the water toward Jesus. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "But when he saw the strong[[COMMENT(0)]] wind and the waves, he was
        terrified and began to sink. \u201CSave me, Lord!\u201D he shouted.  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:30 '
        content: Some manuscripts do not include <b>strong.</b>
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Jesus immediately reached out and grabbed him. <JESUS>\u201CYou have
        so little faith,\u201D </JESUS>Jesus said. <JESUS>\u201CWhy did you doubt
        me?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'When they climbed back into the boat, the wind stopped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then the disciples worshiped him. \u201CYou really are the Son of
        God!\u201D they exclaimed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'After they had crossed the lake, they landed at Gennesaret. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'When the people recognized Jesus, the news of his arrival spread
        quickly throughout the whole area, and soon people were bringing all their
        sick to be healed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: They begged him to let the sick touch at least the fringe of his robe,
        and all who touched him were healed.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Teaches about Inner Purity'
      title: Jesus Teaches about Inner Purity
      number: 1
      content: '  Some Pharisees and teachers of religious law now arrived from Jerusalem
        to see Jesus. They asked him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CWhy do your disciples disobey our age-old tradition? For they
        ignore our tradition of ceremonial hand washing before they eat.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CAnd why do you, by your traditions, violate
        the direct commandments of God?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "<JESUS>For instance, God says, \u2018Honor your father and mother,\u2019</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>and \u2018Anyone who speaks disrespectfully of father or mother must
        be put to death.\u2019</JESUS>[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:4a '
        content: Exod 20:12; Deut 5:16.
      - number: '15:4b '
        content: Exod 21:17 (Greek version); Lev 20:9 (Greek version).
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "<JESUS>But you say it is all right for people to say to their parents,
        \u2018Sorry, I can\u2019t help you. For I have vowed to give to God what
        I would have given to you.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "<JESUS>In this way, you say they don\u2019t need to honor their parents.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>And so you cancel the word of God for the sake of your own tradition.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:6 '
        content: 'Greek <b>their father; </b>other manuscripts read <b>their father
          or their mother.</b>  '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '<JESUS>You hypocrites! Isaiah was right when he prophesied about
        you, for he wrote,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  <JESUS>\u2018These people honor me with their lips,</JESUS>  <JESUS>but
        their hearts are far from me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  <JESUS>Their worship is a farce,</JESUS>  <JESUS>for they teach
        man-made ideas as commands from God.\u2019</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:8-9 '
        content: '  Isa 29:13 (Greek version).  '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Jesus called to the crowd to come and hear. <JESUS>\u201CListen,\u201D
        </JESUS>he said, <JESUS>\u201Cand try to understand.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "<JESUS>It\u2019s not what goes into your mouth that defiles you;
        you are defiled by the words that come out of your mouth.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the disciples came to him and asked, \u201CDo you realize you
        offended the Pharisees by what you just said?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CEvery plant not planted by my heavenly
        Father will be uprooted,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "<JESUS>so ignore them. They are blind guides leading the blind, and
        if one blind person guides another, they will both fall into a ditch.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Peter said to Jesus, \u201CExplain to us the parable that says
        people aren\u2019t defiled by what they eat.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t you understand yet?\u201D </JESUS>Jesus
        asked. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CAnything you eat passes through the stomach and then
        goes into the sewer.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>But the words you speak come from the heart\u2014that\u2019s
        what defiles you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '<JESUS>For from the heart come evil thoughts, murder, adultery, all
        sexual immorality, theft, lying, and slander.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: The Faith of a Gentile Woman'
      title: The Faith of a Gentile Woman
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>These are what defile you. Eating with unwashed hands will
        never defile you.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then Jesus left Galilee and went north to the region of Tyre and
        Sidon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "A Gentile[[COMMENT(0)]] woman who lived there came to him, pleading,
        \u201CHave mercy on me, O Lord, Son of David! For my daughter is possessed
        by a demon that torments her severely.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:22 '
        content: Greek <b>Canaanite.</b>
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But Jesus gave her no reply, not even a word. Then his disciples
        urged him to send her away. \u201CTell her to go away,\u201D they said. \u201CShe
        is bothering us with all her begging.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Jesus said to the woman, <JESUS>\u201CI was sent only to help
        God\u2019s lost sheep\u2014the people of Israel.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But she came and worshiped him, pleading again, \u201CLord, help
        me!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CIt isn\u2019t right to take food from
        the children and throw it to the dogs.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "She replied, \u201CThat\u2019s true, Lord, but even dogs are allowed
        to eat the scraps that fall beneath their masters\u2019 table.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: Jesus Heals Many People'
      title: Jesus Heals Many People
      number: 28
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CDear woman,\u201D </JESUS>Jesus said to her, <JESUS>\u201Cyour
        faith is great. Your request is granted.\u201D</JESUS> And her daughter was
        instantly healed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Jesus returned to the Sea of Galilee and climbed a hill and sat down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "A vast crowd brought to him people who were lame, blind, crippled,
        those who couldn\u2019t speak, and many others. They laid them before Jesus,
        and he healed them all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: Jesus Feeds Four Thousand'
      title: Jesus Feeds Four Thousand
      number: 31
      content: "The crowd was amazed! Those who hadn\u2019t been able to speak were
        talking, the crippled were made well, the lame were walking, and the blind
        could see again! And they praised the God of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then Jesus called his disciples and told them, <JESUS>\u201CI feel
        sorry for these people. They have been here with me for three days, and they
        have nothing left to eat. I don\u2019t want to send them away hungry, or
        they will faint along the way.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "The disciples replied, \u201CWhere would we get enough food here
        in the wilderness for such a huge crowd?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Jesus asked, <JESUS>\u201CHow much bread do you have?\u201D</JESUS>They
        replied, \u201CSeven loaves, and a few small fish.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'So Jesus told all the people to sit down on the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Then he took the seven loaves and the fish, thanked God for them,
        and broke them into pieces. He gave them to the disciples, who distributed
        the food to the crowd.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'They all ate as much as they wanted. Afterward, the disciples picked
        up seven large baskets of leftover food. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'There were 4,000 men who were fed that day, in addition to all the
        women and children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: Then Jesus sent the people home, and he got into a boat and crossed
        over to the region of Magadan.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Leaders Demand a Miraculous Sign'
      title: Leaders Demand a Miraculous Sign
      number: 1
      content: '  One day the Pharisees and Sadducees came to test Jesus, demanding
        that he show them a miraculous sign from heaven to prove his authority.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He replied, <JESUS>\u201CYou know the saying, \u2018Red sky at night
        means fair weather tomorrow;</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "<JESUS>red sky in the morning means foul weather all day.\u2019 You
        know how to interpret the weather signs in the sky, but you don\u2019t know
        how to interpret the signs of the times!</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:2-3 '
        content: Several manuscripts do not include any of the words in 16:2-3 after
          <b>He replied.</b>
    - name: '4: Yeast of the Pharisees and Sadducees'
      title: Yeast of the Pharisees and Sadducees
      number: 4
      content: "<JESUS>Only an evil, adulterous generation would demand a miraculous
        sign, but the only sign I will give them is the sign of the prophet Jonah.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>\u201D</JESUS>
        Then Jesus left them and went away.  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:4 '
        content: Greek <b>the sign of Jonah.</b>
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Later, after they crossed to the other side of the lake, the disciples
        discovered they had forgotten to bring any bread. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CWatch out!\u201D </JESUS>Jesus warned them. <JESUS>\u201CBeware
        of the yeast of the Pharisees and Sadducees.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "At this they began to argue with each other because they hadn\u2019t
        brought any bread. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Jesus knew what they were saying, so he said, <JESUS>\u201CYou have
        so little faith! Why are you arguing with each other about having no bread?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "<JESUS>Don\u2019t you understand even yet? Don\u2019t you remember
        the 5,000 I fed with five loaves, and the baskets of leftovers you picked
        up?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '<JESUS>Or the 4,000 I fed with seven loaves, and the large baskets
        of leftovers you picked up?</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "<JESUS>Why can\u2019t you understand that I\u2019m not talking about
        bread? So again I say, \u2018Beware of the yeast of the Pharisees and Sadducees.\u2019\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: "12: Peter\u2019s Declaration about Jesus"
      title: "Peter\u2019s Declaration about Jesus"
      number: 12
      content: "Then at last they understood that he wasn\u2019t speaking about the
        yeast in bread, but about the deceptive teaching of the Pharisees and Sadducees.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "When Jesus came to the region of Caesarea Philippi, he asked his
        disciples, <JESUS>\u201CWho do people say that the Son of Man is?\u201D</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:13 '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CWell,\u201D they replied, \u201Csome say John the Baptist,
        some say Elijah, and others say Jeremiah or one of the other prophets.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then he asked them, <JESUS>\u201CBut who do you say I am?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Simon Peter answered, \u201CYou are the Messiah,[[COMMENT(0)]] the
        Son of the living God.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:16 '
        content: "Or <b>the Christ. </b><b>Messiah </b>(a Hebrew term) and <b>Christ
          </b>(a Greek term) both mean \u201Canointed one.\u201D"
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CYou are blessed, Simon son of John,</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>because my Father in heaven has revealed this to you. You did not
        learn this from any human being.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:17 '
        content: Greek <b>Simon bar-Jonah; </b>see John 1:42; 21:15-17.
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>Now I say to you that you are Peter (which means \u2018rock\u2019),</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>and upon this rock I will build my church, and all the powers of hell</JESUS>[[COMMENT(1)]] 
        <JESUS>will not conquer it.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:18a '
        content: Greek <b>that you are Peter.</b>
      - number: '16:18b '
        content: Greek <b>and the gates of Hades.</b>
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>And I will give you the keys of the Kingdom of Heaven. Whatever
        you forbid</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>on earth will be forbidden in heaven,
        and whatever you permit</JESUS>[[COMMENT(1)]]  <JESUS>on earth will be permitted
        in heaven.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:19a '
        content: Or <b>bind, </b>or <b>lock.</b>
      - number: '16:19b '
        content: Or <b>loose, </b>or <b>open</b>.
    - name: '20: Jesus Predicts His Death'
      title: Jesus Predicts His Death
      number: 20
      content: 'Then he sternly warned the disciples not to tell anyone that he was
        the Messiah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'From then on Jesus[[COMMENT(0)]] began to tell his disciples plainly
        that it was necessary for him to go to Jerusalem, and that he would suffer
        many terrible things at the hands of the elders, the leading priests, and
        the teachers of religious law. He would be killed, but on the third day he
        would be raised from the dead.  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:21 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>Jesus the Messiah.</b>
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But Peter took him aside and began to reprimand him[[COMMENT(0)]]
        for saying such things. \u201CHeaven forbid, Lord,\u201D he said. \u201CThis
        will never happen to you!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:22 '
        content: Or <b>began to correct him.</b>
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Jesus turned to Peter and said, <JESUS>\u201CGet away from me, Satan!
        You are a dangerous trap to me. You are seeing things merely from a human
        point of view, not from God\u2019s.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Jesus said to his disciples, <JESUS>\u201CIf any of you wants
        to be my follower, you must give up your own way, take up your cross, and
        follow me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '<JESUS>If you try to hang on to your life, you will lose it. But
        if you give up your life for my sake, you will save it.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '<JESUS>And what do you benefit if you gain the whole world but lose
        your own soul?</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>Is anything worth more than
        your soul?</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:26 '
        content: Or <b>your self? </b>also in 16:26b.
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '<JESUS>For the Son of Man will come with his angels in the glory
        of his Father and will judge all people according to their deeds.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "<JESUS>And I tell you the truth, some standing here right now will
        not die before they see the Son of Man coming in his Kingdom.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Transfiguration'
      title: The Transfiguration
      number: 1
      content: '  Six days later Jesus took Peter and the two brothers, James and
        John, and led them up a high mountain to be alone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "As the men watched, Jesus\u2019 appearance was transformed so that
        his face shone like the sun, and his clothes became as white as light. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Suddenly, Moses and Elijah appeared and began talking with Jesus.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Peter exclaimed, \u201CLord, it\u2019s wonderful for us to be here!
        If you want, I\u2019ll make three shelters as memorials[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014one
        for you, one for Moses, and one for Elijah.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:4 '
        content: Greek <b>three tabernacles.</b>
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But even as he spoke, a bright cloud overshadowed them, and a voice
        from the cloud said, \u201CThis is my dearly loved Son, who brings me great
        joy. Listen to him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The disciples were terrified and fell face down on the ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Jesus came over and touched them. <JESUS>\u201CGet up,\u201D
        </JESUS>he said. <JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t be afraid.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And when they looked up, Moses and Elijah were gone, and they saw
        only Jesus.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "As they went back down the mountain, Jesus commanded them, <JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t
        tell anyone what you have seen until the Son of Man</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>has been raised from the dead.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:9 '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then his disciples asked him, \u201CWhy do the teachers of religious
        law insist that Elijah must return before the Messiah comes?[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:10 '
        content: Greek <b>that Elijah must come first?</b>
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CElijah is indeed coming first to get
        everything ready.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "<JESUS>But I tell you, Elijah has already come, but he wasn\u2019t
        recognized, and they chose to abuse him. And in the same way they will also
        make the Son of Man suffer.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Jesus Heals a Demon-Possessed Boy'
      title: Jesus Heals a Demon-Possessed Boy
      number: 13
      content: 'Then the disciples realized he was talking about John the Baptist.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'At the foot of the mountain, a large crowd was waiting for them.
        A man came and knelt before Jesus and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CLord, have mercy on my son. He has seizures and suffers terribly.
        He often falls into the fire or into the water. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So I brought him to your disciples, but they couldn\u2019t heal him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CYou faithless and corrupt people! How long
        must I be with you? How long must I put up with you? Bring the boy here to
        me.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then Jesus rebuked the demon in the boy, and it left him. From that
        moment the boy was well.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Afterward the disciples asked Jesus privately, \u201CWhy couldn\u2019t
        we cast out that demon?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Jesus Again Predicts His Death'
      title: Jesus Again Predicts His Death
      number: 20
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CYou don\u2019t have enough faith,\u201D </JESUS>Jesus
        told them. <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth, if you had faith even as small
        as a mustard seed, you could say to this mountain, \u2018Move from here to
        there,\u2019 and it would move. Nothing would be impossible.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:20 '
        content: "Some manuscripts add verse 21, <b>But this kind of demon won\u2019t
          leave except by prayer and fasting. </b>Compare Mark 9:29."
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "After they gathered again in Galilee, Jesus told them, <JESUS>\u201CThe
        Son of Man is going to be betrayed into the hands of his enemies.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Payment of the Temple Tax'
      title: Payment of the Temple Tax
      number: 23
      content: "<JESUS>He will be killed, but on the third day he will be raised
        from the dead.\u201D</JESUS> And the disciples were filled with grief.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "On their arrival in Capernaum, the collectors of the Temple tax[[COMMENT(0)]]
        came to Peter and asked him, \u201CDoesn\u2019t your teacher pay the Temple
        tax?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:24 '
        content: Greek <b>the two-drachma [tax]; </b>also in 17:24b. See Exod 30:13-16;
          Neh 10:32-33.
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CYes, he does,\u201D Peter replied. Then he went into the house.But
        before he had a chance to speak, Jesus asked him, <JESUS>\u201CWhat do you
        think, Peter?</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>Do kings tax their own people
        or the people they have conquered?</JESUS>[[COMMENT(1)]]<JESUS>\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:25a '
        content: Greek <b>Simon?</b>
      - number: '17:25b '
        content: Greek <b>their sons or others?</b>
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CThey tax the people they have conquered,\u201D Peter replied. 
        <JESUS>\u201CWell, then,\u201D </JESUS>Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201Cthe citizens
        are free!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "<JESUS>However, we don\u2019t want to offend them, so go down to
        the lake and throw in a line. Open the mouth of the first fish you catch,
        and you will find a large silver coin.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>Take
        it and pay the tax for both of us.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: '17:27 '
        content: Greek <b>a stater </b>[a Greek coin equivalent to four drachmas].
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Greatest in the Kingdom'
      title: The Greatest in the Kingdom
      number: 1
      content: "  About that time the disciples came to Jesus and asked, \u201CWho
        is greatest in the Kingdom of Heaven?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Jesus called a little child to him and put the child among them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then he said, <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth, unless you turn
        from your sins and become like little children, you will never get into the
        Kingdom of Heaven.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '<JESUS>So anyone who becomes as humble as this little child is the
        greatest in the Kingdom of Heaven.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CAnd anyone who welcomes a little child like this on
        my behalf</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>is welcoming me.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:5 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>in my name.</b>  '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '<JESUS>But if you cause one of these little ones who trusts in me
        to fall into sin, it would be better for you to have a large millstone tied
        around your neck and be drowned in the depths of the sea.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CWhat sorrow awaits the world, because it tempts people
        to sin. Temptations are inevitable, but what sorrow awaits the person who
        does the tempting.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>So if your hand or foot causes you to sin, cut it off and
        throw it away. It\u2019s better to enter eternal life with only one hand
        or one foot than to be thrown into eternal fire with both of your hands and
        feet.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "<JESUS>And if your eye causes you to sin, gouge it out and throw
        it away. It\u2019s better to enter eternal life with only one eye than to
        have two eyes and be thrown into the fire of hell.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:9 '
        content: 'Greek <b>the Gehenna of fire.</b>  '
    - name: '10: Parable of the Lost Sheep'
      title: Parable of the Lost Sheep
      number: 10
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBeware that you don\u2019t look down on any of these
        little ones. For I tell you that in heaven their angels are always in the
        presence of my heavenly Father.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:10 '
        content: '  Some manuscripts add verse 11,   <b>And the Son of Man came to
          save those who are lost. </b>  Compare Luke 19:10.    '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CIf a man has a hundred sheep and one of them wanders
        away, what will he do? Won\u2019t he leave the ninety-nine others on the
        hills and go out to search for the one that is lost?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "<JESUS>And if he finds it, I tell you the truth, he will rejoice
        over it more than over the ninety-nine that didn\u2019t wander away!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Correcting Another Believer'
      title: Correcting Another Believer
      number: 14
      content: "<JESUS>In the same way, it is not my heavenly Father\u2019s will
        that even one of these little ones should perish.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CIf another believer</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>sins
        against you,</JESUS>[[COMMENT(1)]]  <JESUS>go privately and point out the
        offense. If the other person listens and confesses it, you have won that
        person back.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:15a '
        content: '  Greek   <b>If your brother.</b>  '
      - number: '18:15b '
        content: 'Some manuscripts do not include <b>against you.</b>  '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '<JESUS>But if you are unsuccessful, take one or two others with you
        and go back again, so that everything you say may be confirmed by two or
        three witnesses.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "<JESUS>If the person still refuses to listen, take your case to the
        church. Then if he or she won\u2019t accept the church\u2019s decision, treat
        that person as a pagan or a corrupt tax collector.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth, whatever you forbid</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>on earth will be forbidden in heaven, and whatever
        you permit</JESUS>[[COMMENT(1)]]  <JESUS>on earth will be permitted in heaven.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:18a '
        content: '  Or   <b>bind, </b>  or   <b>lock.</b>  '
      - number: '18:18b '
        content: Or <b>loose, </b>or <b>open.</b>
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI also tell you this: If two of you agree here on
        earth concerning anything you ask, my Father in heaven will do it for you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Parable of the Unforgiving Debtor'
      title: Parable of the Unforgiving Debtor
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>For where two or three gather together as my followers,</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>I am there among them.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:20 '
        content: Greek <b>gather together in my name.</b>
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Peter came to him and asked, \u201CLord, how often should I
        forgive someone[[COMMENT(0)]] who sins against me? Seven times?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:21 '
        content: Greek <b>my brother.</b>
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CNo, not seven times,\u201D </JESUS>Jesus replied,
        <JESUS>\u201Cbut seventy times seven!</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:22 '
        content: Or <b>seventy-seven times.</b>
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CTherefore, the Kingdom of Heaven can be compared to
        a king who decided to bring his accounts up to date with servants who had
        borrowed money from him.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '<JESUS>In the process, one of his debtors was brought in who owed
        him millions of dollars.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '18:24 '
        content: 'Greek <b>10,000 talents </b>[375 tons or 340 metric tons of silver].  '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "<JESUS>He couldn\u2019t pay, so his master ordered that he be sold\u2014along
        with his wife, his children, and everything he owned\u2014to pay the debt.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBut the man fell down before his master and begged
        him, \u2018Please, be patient with me, and I will pay it all.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '<JESUS>Then his master was filled with pity for him, and he released
        him and forgave his debt.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBut when the man left the king, he went to a fellow
        servant who owed him a few thousand dollars.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>He
        grabbed him by the throat and demanded instant payment.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:28 '
        content: "  Greek   <b>100 denarii. </b>  A denarius was equivalent to a
          laborer\u2019s full day\u2019s wage.    "
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CHis fellow servant fell down before him and begged
        for a little more time. \u2018Be patient with me, and I will pay it,\u2019
        he pleaded.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "<JESUS>But his creditor wouldn\u2019t wait. He had the man arrested
        and put in prison until the debt could be paid in full.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CWhen some of the other servants saw this, they were
        very upset. They went to the king and told him everything that had happened.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "<JESUS>Then the king called in the man he had forgiven and said,
        \u2018You evil servant! I forgave you that tremendous debt because you pleaded
        with me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "<JESUS>Shouldn\u2019t you have mercy on your fellow servant, just
        as I had mercy on you?\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: '<JESUS>Then the angry king sent the man to prison to be tortured
        until he had paid his entire debt.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThat\u2019s what my heavenly Father will do to you
        if you refuse to forgive your brothers and sisters</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>from your heart.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: '18:35 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>your brother.</b>  '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Discussion about Divorce and Marriage'
      title: Discussion about Divorce and Marriage
      number: 1
      content: '  When Jesus had finished saying these things, he left Galilee and
        went down to the region of Judea east of the Jordan River. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Large crowds followed him there, and he healed their sick.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Some Pharisees came and tried to trap him with this question: \u201CShould
        a man be allowed to divorce his wife for just any reason?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CHaven\u2019t you read the Scriptures?\u201D </JESUS>Jesus
        replied. <JESUS>\u201CThey record that from the beginning \u2018God made
        them male and female.\u2019</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:4 '
        content: Gen 1:27; 5:2.
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And he said, <JESUS>\u201C\u2018This explains why a man leaves his
        father and mother and is joined to his wife, and the two are united into
        one.\u2019</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:5 '
        content: Gen 2:24.
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "<JESUS>Since they are no longer two but one, let no one split apart
        what God has joined together.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CThen why did Moses say in the law that a man could give his
        wife a written notice of divorce and send her away?\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]] they
        asked.  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:7 '
        content: See Deut 24:1.
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CMoses permitted divorce only as a concession
        to your hard hearts, but it was not what God had originally intended.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "<JESUS>And I tell you this, whoever divorces his wife and marries
        someone else commits adultery\u2014unless his wife has been unfaithful.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:9 '
        content: Some manuscripts add <b>And anyone who marries a divorced woman
          commits adultery. </b>Compare Matt 5:32.
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jesus\u2019 disciples then said to him, \u201CIf this is the case,
        it is better not to marry!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CNot everyone can accept this statement,\u201D </JESUS>Jesus
        said. <JESUS>\u201COnly those whom God helps.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Jesus Blesses the Children'
      title: Jesus Blesses the Children
      number: 12
      content: "<JESUS>Some are born as eunuchs, some have been made eunuchs by others,
        and some choose not to marry</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>for the sake of
        the Kingdom of Heaven. Let anyone accept this who can.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:12 '
        content: Greek <b>and some make themselves eunuchs.</b>
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'One day some parents brought their children to Jesus so he could
        lay his hands on them and pray for them. But the disciples scolded the parents
        for bothering him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CLet the children come to me. Don\u2019t
        stop them! For the Kingdom of Heaven belongs to those who are like these
        children.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Rich Man'
      title: The Rich Man
      number: 15
      content: 'And he placed his hands on their heads and blessed them before he
        left.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Someone came to Jesus with this question: \u201CTeacher,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        what good deed must I do to have eternal life?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:16 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>Good Teacher.</b>
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CWhy ask me about what is good?\u201D </JESUS>Jesus
        replied. <JESUS>\u201CThere is only One who is good. But to answer your question\u2014if
        you want to receive eternal life, keep</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>the
        commandments.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:17 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>continue to keep.</b>
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CWhich ones?\u201D the man asked.And Jesus replied: <JESUS>\u201C\u2018You
        must not murder. You must not commit adultery. You must not steal. You must
        not testify falsely.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>Honor your father and mother. Love your neighbor as yourself.\u2019</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:18-19 '
        content: Exod 20:12-16; Deut 5:16-20; Lev 19:18.
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CI\u2019ve obeyed all these commandments,\u201D the young man
        replied. \u201CWhat else must I do?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Jesus told him, <JESUS>\u201CIf you want to be perfect, go and sell
        all your possessions and give the money to the poor, and you will have treasure
        in heaven. Then come, follow me.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But when the young man heard this, he went away sad, for he had many
        possessions.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Jesus said to his disciples, <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth,
        it is very hard for a rich person to enter the Kingdom of Heaven.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>I\u2019ll say it again\u2014it is easier for a camel to go
        through the eye of a needle than for a rich person to enter the Kingdom of
        God!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The disciples were astounded. \u201CThen who in the world can be
        saved?\u201D they asked.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Jesus looked at them intently and said, <JESUS>\u201CHumanly speaking,
        it is impossible. But with God everything is possible.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then Peter said to him, \u201CWe\u2019ve given up everything to follow
        you. What will we get?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CI assure you that when the world is made
        new</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and the Son of Man</JESUS>[[COMMENT(1)]] 
        <JESUS>sits upon his glorious throne, you who have been my followers will
        also sit on twelve thrones, judging the twelve tribes of Israel.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:28a '
        content: Or <b>in the regeneration.</b>
      - number: '19:28b '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '<JESUS>And everyone who has given up houses or brothers or sisters
        or father or mother or children or property, for my sake, will receive a
        hundred times as much in return and will inherit eternal life.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: <JESUS>But many who are the greatest now will be least important then,
        and those who seem least important now will be the greatest then.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: '19:30 '
        content: Greek <b>But many who are first will be last; and the last, first.</b>
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Parable of the Vineyard Workers'
      title: Parable of the Vineyard Workers
      number: 1
      content: "    <JESUS>\u201CFor the Kingdom of Heaven is like the landowner
        who went out early one morning to hire workers for his vineyard.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '<JESUS>He agreed to pay the normal daily wage</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>and sent them out to work.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '20:2 '
        content: "Greek <b>a denarius, </b>the payment for a full day\u2019s labor;
          similarly in 20:9, 10, 13."
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CAt nine o\u2019clock in the morning he was passing
        through the marketplace and saw some people standing around doing nothing.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '<JESUS>So he hired them, telling them he would pay them whatever
        was right at the end of the day.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "<JESUS>So they went to work in the vineyard. At noon and again at
        three o\u2019clock he did the same thing.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CAt five o\u2019clock that afternoon he was in town
        again and saw some more people standing around. He asked them, \u2018Why
        haven\u2019t you been working today?\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThey replied, \u2018Because no one hired us.\u2019</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>\u201CThe landowner told them, \u2018Then go out and join the others
        in my vineyard.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThat evening he told the foreman to call the workers
        in and pay them, beginning with the last workers first.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "<JESUS>When those hired at five o\u2019clock were paid, each received
        a full day\u2019s wage.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>When those hired first came to get their pay, they assumed
        they would receive more. But they, too, were paid a day\u2019s wage.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '<JESUS>When they received their pay, they protested to the owner,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "<JESUS>\u2018Those people worked only one hour, and yet you\u2019ve
        paid them just as much as you paid us who worked all day in the scorching
        heat.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CHe answered one of them, \u2018Friend, I haven\u2019t
        been unfair! Didn\u2019t you agree to work all day for the usual wage?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '<JESUS>Take your money and go. I wanted to pay this last worker the
        same as you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "<JESUS>Is it against the law for me to do what I want with my money?
        Should you be jealous because I am kind to others?\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Jesus Again Predicts His Death'
      title: Jesus Again Predicts His Death
      number: 16
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CSo those who are last now will be first then, and
        those who are first will be last.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'As Jesus was going up to Jerusalem, he took the twelve disciples
        aside privately and told them what was going to happen to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CListen,\u201D </JESUS>he said, <JESUS>\u201Cwe\u2019re
        going up to Jerusalem, where the Son of Man</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>will
        be betrayed to the leading priests and the teachers of religious law. They
        will sentence him to die.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '20:18 '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - name: '19: Jesus Teaches about Serving Others'
      title: Jesus Teaches about Serving Others
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>Then they will hand him over to the Romans</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>to be mocked, flogged with a whip, and crucified. But on the third
        day he will be raised from the dead.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '20:19 '
        content: Greek <b>the Gentiles.</b>
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then the mother of James and John, the sons of Zebedee, came to Jesus
        with her sons. She knelt respectfully to ask a favor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CWhat is your request?\u201D </JESUS>he asked.She replied,
        \u201CIn your Kingdom, please let my two sons sit in places of honor next
        to you, one on your right and the other on your left.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But Jesus answered by saying to them, <JESUS>\u201CYou don\u2019t
        know what you are asking! Are you able to drink from the bitter cup of suffering
        I am about to drink?\u201D</JESUS>\u201COh yes,\u201D they replied, \u201Cwe
        are able!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Jesus told them, <JESUS>\u201CYou will indeed drink from my bitter
        cup. But I have no right to say who will sit on my right or my left. My Father
        has prepared those places for the ones he has chosen.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When the ten other disciples heard what James and John had asked,
        they were indignant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But Jesus called them together and said, <JESUS>\u201CYou know that
        the rulers in this world lord it over their people, and officials flaunt
        their authority over those under them.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '<JESUS>But among you it will be different. Whoever wants to be a
        leader among you must be your servant,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '<JESUS>and whoever wants to be first among you must become your slave.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: Jesus Heals Two Blind Men'
      title: Jesus Heals Two Blind Men
      number: 28
      content: "<JESUS>For even the Son of Man came not to be served but to serve
        others and to give his life as a ransom for many.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'As Jesus and the disciples left the town of Jericho, a large crowd
        followed behind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Two blind men were sitting beside the road. When they heard that
        Jesus was coming that way, they began shouting, \u201CLord, Son of David,
        have mercy on us!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CBe quiet!\u201D the crowd yelled at them.But they only shouted
        louder, \u201CLord, Son of David, have mercy on us!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "When Jesus heard them, he stopped and called, <JESUS>\u201CWhat do
        you want me to do for you?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CLord,\u201D they said, \u201Cwe want to see!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: Jesus felt sorry for them and touched their eyes. Instantly they could
        see! Then they followed him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jesus\u2019 Triumphant Entry"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 Triumphant Entry"
      number: 1
      content: '  As Jesus and the disciples approached Jerusalem, they came to the
        town of Bethphage on the Mount of Olives. Jesus sent two of them on ahead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CGo into the village over there,\u201D </JESUS>he said.
        <JESUS>\u201CAs soon as you enter it, you will see a donkey tied there, with
        its colt beside it. Untie them and bring them to me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "<JESUS>If anyone asks what you are doing, just say, \u2018The Lord
        needs them,\u2019 and he will immediately let you take them.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'This took place to fulfill the prophecy that said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CTell the people of Jerusalem,[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2018Look, your
        King is coming to you.He is humble, riding on a donkey\u2014riding on a donkey\u2019s
        colt.\u2019\u201D[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:5a '
        content: Greek <b>Tell the daughter of Zion. </b>Isa 62:11.
      - number: '21:5b '
        content: Zech 9:9.
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The two disciples did as Jesus commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They brought the donkey and the colt to him and threw their garments
        over the colt, and he sat on it.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '21:7 '
        content: Greek <b>over them, and he sat on them.</b>
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Most of the crowd spread their garments on the road ahead of him,
        and others cut branches from the trees and spread them on the road. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Jesus was in the center of the procession, and the people all around
        him were shouting,\u201CPraise God[[COMMENT(0)]] for the Son of David!Blessings
        on the one who comes in the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!Praise
        God in highest heaven!\u201D[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:9a '
        content: "Greek <b>Hosanna, </b>an exclamation of praise that literally means
          \u201Csave now\u201D; also in 21:9b, 15."
      - number: '21:9b '
        content: Pss 118:25-26; 148:1.
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The entire city of Jerusalem was in an uproar as he entered. \u201CWho
        is this?\u201D they asked.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Jesus Clears the Temple'
      title: Jesus Clears the Temple
      number: 11
      content: "And the crowds replied, \u201CIt\u2019s Jesus, the prophet from Nazareth
        in Galilee.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Jesus entered the Temple and began to drive out all the people buying
        and selling animals for sacrifice. He knocked over the tables of the money
        changers and the chairs of those selling doves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CThe Scriptures declare, \u2018My Temple
        will be called a house of prayer,\u2019 but you have turned it into a den
        of thieves!\u201D</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:13 '
        content: Isa 56:7; Jer 7:11.
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The blind and the lame came to him in the Temple, and he healed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The leading priests and the teachers of religious law saw these wonderful
        miracles and heard even the children in the Temple shouting, \u201CPraise
        God for the Son of David.\u201DBut the leaders were indignant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "They asked Jesus, \u201CDo you hear what these children are saying?\u201D 
        <JESUS>\u201CYes,\u201D </JESUS>Jesus replied. <JESUS>\u201CHaven\u2019t
        you ever read the Scriptures? For they say, \u2018You have taught children
        and infants to give you praise.\u2019</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:16 '
        content: Ps 8:2 (Greek version).
    - name: '17: Jesus Curses the Fig Tree'
      title: Jesus Curses the Fig Tree
      number: 17
      content: 'Then he returned to Bethany, where he stayed overnight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'In the morning, as Jesus was returning to Jerusalem, he was hungry, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and he noticed a fig tree beside the road. He went over to see if
        there were any figs, but there were only leaves. Then he said to it, <JESUS>\u201CMay
        you never bear fruit again!\u201D</JESUS> And immediately the fig tree withered
        up.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "The disciples were amazed when they saw this and asked, \u201CHow
        did the fig tree wither so quickly?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Jesus told them, <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth, if you have
        faith and don\u2019t doubt, you can do things like this and much more. You
        can even say to this mountain, \u2018May you be lifted up and thrown into
        the sea,\u2019 and it will happen.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: The Authority of Jesus Challenged'
      title: The Authority of Jesus Challenged
      number: 22
      content: "<JESUS>You can pray for anything, and if you have faith, you will
        receive it.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "When Jesus returned to the Temple and began teaching, the leading
        priests and elders came up to him. They demanded, \u201CBy what authority
        are you doing all these things? Who gave you the right?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI\u2019ll tell you by what authority I do these things
        if you answer one question,\u201D </JESUS>Jesus replied. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CDid John\u2019s authority to baptize come from heaven,
        or was it merely human?\u201D</JESUS>They talked it over among themselves.
        \u201CIf we say it was from heaven, he will ask us why we didn\u2019t believe
        John. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But if we say it was merely human, we\u2019ll be mobbed because the
        people believe John was a prophet.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Parable of the Two Sons'
      title: Parable of the Two Sons
      number: 27
      content: "So they finally replied, \u201CWe don\u2019t know.\u201DAnd Jesus
        responded, <JESUS>\u201CThen I won\u2019t tell you by what authority I do
        these things.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBut what do you think about this? A man with two sons
        told the older boy, \u2018Son, go out and work in the vineyard today.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "<JESUS>The son answered, \u2018No, I won\u2019t go,\u2019 but later
        he changed his mind and went anyway.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "<JESUS>Then the father told the other son, \u2018You go,\u2019 and
        he said, \u2018Yes, sir, I will.\u2019 But he didn\u2019t go.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CWhich of the two obeyed his father?\u201D</JESUS>They
        replied, \u201CThe first.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]Then Jesus explained his meaning:
        <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth, corrupt tax collectors and prostitutes
        will get into the Kingdom of God before you do.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:29-31 '
        content: "Other manuscripts read <b>\u201CThe second.\u201D </b>In still
          other manuscripts the first son says \u201CYes\u201D but does nothing,
          the second son says \u201CNo\u201D but then repents and goes, and the answer
          to Jesus\u2019 question is that the second son obeyed his father.  "
    - name: '32: Parable of the Evil Farmers'
      title: Parable of the Evil Farmers
      number: 32
      content: "<JESUS>For John the Baptist came and showed you the right way to
        live, but you didn\u2019t believe him, while tax collectors and prostitutes
        did. And even when you saw this happening, you refused to believe him and
        repent of your sins.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CNow listen to another story. A certain landowner planted
        a vineyard, built a wall around it, dug a pit for pressing out the grape
        juice, and built a lookout tower. Then he leased the vineyard to tenant farmers
        and moved to another country.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: '<JESUS>At the time of the grape harvest, he sent his servants to
        collect his share of the crop.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: '<JESUS>But the farmers grabbed his servants, beat one, killed one,
        and stoned another.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: '<JESUS>So the landowner sent a larger group of his servants to collect
        for him, but the results were the same.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CFinally, the owner sent his son, thinking, \u2018Surely
        they will respect my son.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBut when the tenant farmers saw his son coming, they
        said to one another, \u2018Here comes the heir to this estate. Come on, let\u2019s
        kill him and get the estate for ourselves!\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: '<JESUS>So they grabbed him, dragged him out of the vineyard, and
        murdered him.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CWhen the owner of the vineyard returns,\u201D </JESUS>Jesus
        asked, <JESUS>\u201Cwhat do you think he will do to those farmers?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "The religious leaders replied, \u201CHe will put the wicked men to
        a horrible death and lease the vineyard to others who will give him his share
        of the crop after each harvest.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Then Jesus asked them, <JESUS>\u201CDidn\u2019t you ever read this
        in the Scriptures?</JESUS>  <JESUS>\u2018The stone that the builders rejected</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>has now become the cornerstone.</JESUS>  <JESUS>This is the </JESUS><smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        doing,  <JESUS>and it is wonderful to see.\u2019</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:42 '
        content: '  Ps 118:22-23.  '
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: '  <JESUS>I tell you, the Kingdom of God will be taken away from you
        and given to a nation that will produce the proper fruit.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "<JESUS>Anyone who stumbles over that stone will be broken to pieces,
        and it will crush anyone it falls on.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:44 '
        content: This verse is not included in some early manuscripts. Compare Luke
          20:18.
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "When the leading priests and Pharisees heard this parable, they realized
        he was telling the story against them\u2014they were the wicked farmers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: They wanted to arrest him, but they were afraid of the crowds, who
        considered Jesus to be a prophet.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Parable of the Great Feast'
      title: Parable of the Great Feast
      number: 1
      content: '  Jesus also told them other parables. He said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe Kingdom of Heaven can be illustrated by the story
        of a king who prepared a great wedding feast for his son.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '<JESUS>When the banquet was ready, he sent his servants to notify
        those who were invited. But they all refused to come!</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CSo he sent other servants to tell them, \u2018The
        feast has been prepared. The bulls and fattened cattle have been killed,
        and everything is ready. Come to the banquet!\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '<JESUS>But the guests he had invited ignored them and went their
        own way, one to his farm, another to his business.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '<JESUS>Others seized his messengers and insulted them and killed
        them.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThe king was furious, and he sent out his army to
        destroy the murderers and burn their town.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>And he said to his servants, \u2018The wedding feast is ready,
        and the guests I invited aren\u2019t worthy of the honor.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "<JESUS>Now go out to the street corners and invite everyone you see.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '<JESUS>So the servants brought in everyone they could find, good
        and bad alike, and the banquet hall was filled with guests.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBut when the king came in to meet the guests, he noticed
        a man who wasn\u2019t wearing the proper clothes for a wedding.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "<JESUS>\u2018Friend,\u2019 he asked, \u2018how is it that you are
        here without wedding clothes?\u2019 But the man had no reply.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "<JESUS>Then the king said to his aides, \u2018Bind his hands and
        feet and throw him into the outer darkness, where there will be weeping and
        gnashing of teeth.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Taxes for Caesar'
      title: Taxes for Caesar
      number: 14
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CFor many are called, but few are chosen.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then the Pharisees met together to plot how to trap Jesus into saying
        something for which he could be arrested. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "They sent some of their disciples, along with the supporters of Herod,
        to meet with him. \u201CTeacher,\u201D they said, \u201Cwe know how honest
        you are. You teach the way of God truthfully. You are impartial and don\u2019t
        play favorites. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Now tell us what you think about this: Is it right to pay taxes to
        Caesar or not?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But Jesus knew their evil motives. <JESUS>\u201CYou hypocrites!\u201D
        </JESUS>he said. <JESUS>\u201CWhy are you trying to trap me?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>Here, show me the coin used for the tax.\u201D</JESUS> When
        they handed him a Roman coin,[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:19 '
        content: Greek <b>a denarius.</b>
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "he asked, <JESUS>\u201CWhose picture and title are stamped on it?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CCaesar\u2019s,\u201D they replied.  <JESUS>\u201CWell, then,\u201D
        </JESUS>he said, <JESUS>\u201Cgive to Caesar what belongs to Caesar, and
        give to God what belongs to God.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Discussion about Resurrection'
      title: Discussion about Resurrection
      number: 22
      content: 'His reply amazed them, and they went away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "That same day Jesus was approached by some Sadducees\u2014religious
        leaders who say there is no resurrection from the dead. They posed this question: "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CTeacher, Moses said, \u2018If a man dies without children,
        his brother should marry the widow and have a child who will carry on the
        brother\u2019s name.\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:24 '
        content: 'Deut 25:5-6.  '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Well, suppose there were seven brothers. The oldest one married and
        then died without children, so his brother married the widow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'But the second brother also died, and the third brother married her.
        This continued with all seven of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Last of all, the woman also died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "So tell us, whose wife will she be in the resurrection? For all seven
        were married to her.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CYour mistake is that you don\u2019t know
        the Scriptures, and you don\u2019t know the power of God.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '<JESUS>For when the dead rise, they will neither marry nor be given
        in marriage. In this respect they will be like the angels in heaven.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBut now, as to whether there will be a resurrection
        of the dead\u2014haven\u2019t you ever read about this in the Scriptures?
        Long after Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob had died, God said,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:31 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>read about this? God said.</b>  '
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "<JESUS>\u2018I am the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God
        of Jacob.\u2019</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>So he is the God of the living,
        not the dead.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:32 '
        content: Exod 3:6.
    - name: '33: The Most Important Commandment'
      title: The Most Important Commandment
      number: 33
      content: 'When the crowds heard him, they were astounded at his teaching.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'But when the Pharisees heard that he had silenced the Sadducees with
        his reply, they met together to question him again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'One of them, an expert in religious law, tried to trap him with this
        question: '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CTeacher, which is the most important commandment in the law
        of Moses?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201C\u2018You must love the </JESUS><smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God with all your heart, all your soul, and all your mind.\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:37 '
        content: Deut 6:5.
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: '<JESUS>This is the first and greatest commandment.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "<JESUS>A second is equally important: \u2018Love your neighbor as
        yourself.\u2019</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:39 '
        content: 'Lev 19:18.  '
    - name: '40: Whose Son Is the Messiah?'
      title: Whose Son Is the Messiah?
      number: 40
      content: "<JESUS>The entire law and all the demands of the prophets are based
        on these two commandments.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Then, surrounded by the Pharisees, Jesus asked them a question: '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CWhat do you think about the Messiah? Whose son is he?\u201D</JESUS>They
        replied, \u201CHe is the son of David.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CThen why does David, speaking under
        the inspiration of the Spirit, call the Messiah \u2018my Lord\u2019? For
        David said,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "  <JESUS>\u2018The </JESUS><smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to my
        Lord,  <JESUS>Sit in the place of honor at my right hand</JESUS>  <JESUS>until
        I humble your enemies beneath your feet.\u2019</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:44 '
        content: '  Ps 110:1.  '
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "  <JESUS>Since David called the Messiah \u2018my Lord,\u2019 how
        can the Messiah be his son?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: No one could answer him. And after that, no one dared to ask him any
        more questions.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Criticizes the Religious Leaders'
      title: Jesus Criticizes the Religious Leaders
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Jesus said to the crowds and to his disciples, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe teachers of religious law and the Pharisees are
        the official interpreters of the law of Moses.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:2 '
        content: 'Greek <b>and the Pharisees sit in the seat of Moses.</b>  '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "<JESUS>So practice and obey whatever they tell you, but don\u2019t
        follow their example. For they don\u2019t practice what they teach.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '<JESUS>They crush people with unbearable religious demands and never
        lift a finger to ease the burden.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CEverything they do is for show. On their arms they
        wear extra wide prayer boxes with Scripture verses inside, and they wear
        robes with extra long tassels.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:5 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>They enlarge their phylacteries and lengthen their
          tassels.</b>  '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '<JESUS>And they love to sit at the head table at banquets and in
        the seats of honor in the synagogues.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "<JESUS>They love to receive respectful greetings as they walk in
        the marketplaces, and to be called \u2018Rabbi.\u2019</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:7 '
        content: "<b>Rabbi, </b>from Aramaic, means \u201Cmaster\u201D or \u201Cteacher.\u201D  "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t let anyone call you \u2018Rabbi,\u2019
        for you have only one teacher, and all of you are equal as brothers and sisters.</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:8 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>brothers.</b>    '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "<JESUS>And don\u2019t address anyone here on earth as \u2018Father,\u2019
        for only God in heaven is your Father.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>And don\u2019t let anyone call you \u2018Teacher,\u2019 for
        you have only one teacher, the Messiah.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '<JESUS>The greatest among you must be a servant.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '<JESUS>But those who exalt themselves will be humbled, and those
        who humble themselves will be exalted.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CWhat sorrow awaits you teachers of religious law and
        you Pharisees. Hypocrites! For you shut the door of the Kingdom of Heaven
        in people\u2019s faces. You won\u2019t go in yourselves, and you don\u2019t
        let others enter either.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:13 '
        content: '  Some manuscripts add verse 14,   <b>What sorrow awaits you teachers
          of religious law and you Pharisees. Hypocrites! You shamelessly cheat widows
          out of their property and then pretend to be pious by making long prayers
          in public. Because of this, you will be severely punished. </b>  Compare
          Mark 12:40 and Luke 20:47.    '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CWhat sorrow awaits you teachers of religious law and
        you Pharisees. Hypocrites! For you cross land and sea to make one convert,
        and then you turn that person into twice the child of hell</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>you yourselves are!</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:15 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>of Gehenna; </b>  also in 23:33.    '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBlind guides! What sorrow awaits you! For you say
        that it means nothing to swear \u2018by God\u2019s Temple,\u2019 but that
        it is binding to swear \u2018by the gold in the Temple.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "<JESUS>Blind fools! Which is more important\u2014the gold or the
        Temple that makes the gold sacred?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>And you say that to swear \u2018by the altar\u2019 is not
        binding, but to swear \u2018by the gifts on the altar\u2019 is binding.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>How blind! For which is more important\u2014the gift on the
        altar or the altar that makes the gift sacred?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>When you swear \u2018by the altar,\u2019 you are swearing
        by it and by everything on it.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>And when you swear \u2018by the Temple,\u2019 you are swearing
        by it and by God, who lives in it.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "<JESUS>And when you swear \u2018by heaven,\u2019 you are swearing
        by the throne of God and by God, who sits on the throne.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CWhat sorrow awaits you teachers of religious law and
        you Pharisees. Hypocrites! For you are careful to tithe even the tiniest
        income from your herb gardens,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>but you ignore
        the more important aspects of the law\u2014justice, mercy, and faith. You
        should tithe, yes, but do not neglect the more important things.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:23 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>tithe the mint, the dill, and the cumin.</b>  '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>Blind guides! You strain your water so you won\u2019t accidentally
        swallow a gnat, but you swallow a camel!</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:24 '
        content: See Lev 11:4, 23, where gnats and camels are both forbidden as food.
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CWhat sorrow awaits you teachers of religious law and
        you Pharisees. Hypocrites! For you are so careful to clean the outside of
        the cup and the dish, but inside you are filthy\u2014full of greed and self-indulgence!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '<JESUS>You blind Pharisee! First wash the inside of the cup and the
        dish,</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and then the outside will become clean,
        too.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:26 '
        content: Some manuscripts do not include <b>and the dish.</b>
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CWhat sorrow awaits you teachers of religious law and
        you Pharisees. Hypocrites! For you are like whitewashed tombs\u2014beautiful
        on the outside but filled on the inside with dead people\u2019s bones and
        all sorts of impurity.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '<JESUS>Outwardly you look like righteous people, but inwardly your
        hearts are filled with hypocrisy and lawlessness.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CWhat sorrow awaits you teachers of religious law and
        you Pharisees. Hypocrites! For you build tombs for the prophets your ancestors
        killed, and you decorate the monuments of the godly people your ancestors
        destroyed.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "<JESUS>Then you say, \u2018If we had lived in the days of our ancestors,
        we would never have joined them in killing the prophets.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBut in saying that, you testify against yourselves
        that you are indeed the descendants of those who murdered the prophets.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: '<JESUS>Go ahead and finish what your ancestors started.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: '<JESUS>Snakes! Sons of vipers! How will you escape the judgment of
        hell?</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CTherefore, I am sending you prophets and wise men
        and teachers of religious law. But you will kill some by crucifixion, and
        you will flog others with whips in your synagogues, chasing them from city
        to city.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "<JESUS>As a result, you will be held responsible for the murder of
        all godly people of all time\u2014from the murder of righteous Abel to the
        murder of Zechariah son of Berekiah, whom you killed in the Temple between
        the sanctuary and the altar.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: Jesus Grieves over Jerusalem'
      title: Jesus Grieves over Jerusalem
      number: 36
      content: '<JESUS>I tell you the truth, this judgment will fall on this very
        generation.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CO Jerusalem, Jerusalem, the city that kills the prophets
        and stones God\u2019s messengers! How often I have wanted to gather your
        children together as a hen protects her chicks beneath her wings, but you
        wouldn\u2019t let me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: '<JESUS>And now, look, your house is abandoned and desolate.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:38 '
        content: Some manuscripts do not include <b>and desolate.</b>
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "<JESUS>For I tell you this, you will never see me again until you
        say, \u2018Blessings on the one who comes in the name of the </JESUS><smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: '23:39 '
        content: Ps 118:26.
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Speaks about the Future'
      title: Jesus Speaks about the Future
      number: 1
      content: '  As Jesus was leaving the Temple grounds, his disciples pointed
        out to him the various Temple buildings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "But he responded, <JESUS>\u201CDo you see all these buildings? I
        tell you the truth, they will be completely demolished. Not one stone will
        be left on top of another!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Later, Jesus sat on the Mount of Olives. His disciples came to him
        privately and said, \u201CTell us, when will all this happen? What sign will
        signal your return and the end of the world?[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '24:3 '
        content: 'Or <b>the age?</b>  '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Jesus told them, <JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t let anyone mislead you,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "<JESUS>for many will come in my name, claiming, \u2018I am the Messiah.\u2019
        They will deceive many.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "<JESUS>And you will hear of wars and threats of wars, but don\u2019t
        panic. Yes, these things must take place, but the end won\u2019t follow immediately.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '<JESUS>Nation will go to war against nation, and kingdom against
        kingdom. There will be famines and earthquakes in many parts of the world.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '<JESUS>But all this is only the first of the birth pains, with more
        to come.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThen you will be arrested, persecuted, and killed.
        You will be hated all over the world because you are my followers.</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '24:9 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>on account of my name.</b>  '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '<JESUS>And many will turn away from me and betray and hate each other.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '<JESUS>And many false prophets will appear and will deceive many
        people.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '<JESUS>Sin will be rampant everywhere, and the love of many will
        grow cold.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '<JESUS>But the one who endures to the end will be saved.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '<JESUS>And the Good News about the Kingdom will be preached throughout
        the whole world, so that all nations</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>will hear
        it; and then the end will come.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:14 '
        content: 'Or <b>all peoples.</b>  '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThe day is coming when you will see what Daniel the
        prophet spoke about\u2014the sacrilegious object that causes desecration</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>standing in the Holy Place.\u201D</JESUS> (Reader,
        pay attention!) "
      comments:
      - number: '24:15 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>the abomination of desolation. </b>  See Dan 9:27;
          11:31; 12:11.  '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThen those in Judea must flee to the hills.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '<JESUS>A person out on the deck of a roof must not go down into the
        house to pack.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '<JESUS>A person out in the field must not return even to get a coat.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '<JESUS>How terrible it will be for pregnant women and for nursing
        mothers in those days.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '<JESUS>And pray that your flight will not be in winter or on the
        Sabbath.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '<JESUS>For there will be greater anguish than at any time since the
        world began. And it will never be so great again.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "<JESUS>In fact, unless that time of calamity is shortened, not a
        single person will survive. But it will be shortened for the sake of God\u2019s
        chosen ones.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThen if anyone tells you, \u2018Look, here is the
        Messiah,\u2019 or \u2018There he is,\u2019 don\u2019t believe it.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>For false messiahs and false prophets will rise up and perform
        great signs and wonders so as to deceive, if possible, even God\u2019s chosen
        ones.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '<JESUS>See, I have warned you about this ahead of time.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CSo if someone tells you, \u2018Look, the Messiah is
        out in the desert,\u2019 don\u2019t bother to go and look. Or, \u2018Look,
        he is hiding here,\u2019 don\u2019t believe it!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '<JESUS>For as the lightning flashes in the east and shines to the
        west, so it will be when the Son of Man</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>comes.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:27 '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '<JESUS>Just as the gathering of vultures shows there is a carcass
        nearby, so these signs indicate that the end is near.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:28 '
        content: 'Greek <b>Wherever the carcass is, the vultures gather.</b>  '
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CImmediately after the anguish of those days,</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>the sun will be darkened,</JESUS>  <JESUS>the moon will give no light,</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>the stars will fall from the sky,</JESUS>  <JESUS>and the powers in
        the heavens will be shaken.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '24:29 '
        content: '  See Isa 13:10; 34:4; Joel 2:10.    '
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '  <JESUS>And then at last, the sign that the Son of Man is coming
        will appear in the heavens, and there will be deep mourning among all the
        peoples of the earth. And they will see the Son of Man coming on the clouds
        of heaven with power and great glory.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:30 '
        content: '  See Dan 7:13.  '
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "<JESUS>And he will send out his angels with the mighty blast of a
        trumpet, and they will gather his chosen ones from all over the world</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>\u2014from
        the farthest ends of the earth and heaven.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '24:31 '
        content: Greek <b>from the four winds.</b>
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CNow learn a lesson from the fig tree. When its branches
        bud and its leaves begin to sprout, you know that summer is near.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: '<JESUS>In the same way, when you see all these things, you can know
        his return is very near, right at the door.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: '<JESUS>I tell you the truth, this generation</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>will not pass from the scene until all these things take place.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:34 '
        content: 'Or <b>this age, </b>or <b>this nation.</b>  '
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: '<JESUS>Heaven and earth will disappear, but my words will never disappear.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CHowever, no one knows the day or hour when these things
        will happen, not even the angels in heaven or the Son himself.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>Only the Father knows.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '24:36 '
        content: '  Some manuscripts do not include   <b>or the Son himself.</b>  '
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CWhen the Son of Man returns, it will be like it was
        in Noah\u2019s day.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: '<JESUS>In those days before the flood, the people were enjoying banquets
        and parties and weddings right up to the time Noah entered his boat.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "<JESUS>People didn\u2019t realize what was going to happen until
        the flood came and swept them all away. That is the way it will be when the
        Son of Man comes.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CTwo men will be working together in the field; one
        will be taken, the other left.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: '<JESUS>Two women will be grinding flour at the mill; one will be
        taken, the other left.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CSo you, too, must keep watch! For you don\u2019t know
        what day your Lord is coming.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: '<JESUS>Understand this: If a homeowner knew exactly when a burglar
        was coming, he would keep watch and not permit his house to be broken into.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: '<JESUS>You also must be ready all the time, for the Son of Man will
        come when least expected.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CA faithful, sensible servant is one to whom the master
        can give the responsibility of managing his other household servants and
        feeding them.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: '<JESUS>If the master returns and finds that the servant has done
        a good job, there will be a reward.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: '<JESUS>I tell you the truth, the master will put that servant in
        charge of all he owns.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "<JESUS>But what if the servant is evil and thinks, \u2018My master
        won\u2019t be back for a while,\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: '<JESUS>and he begins beating the other servants, partying, and getting
        drunk?</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: '<JESUS>The master will return unannounced and unexpected,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: <JESUS>and he will cut the servant to pieces and assign him a place
        with the hypocrites. In that place there will be weeping and gnashing of
        teeth.</JESUS>
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Parable of the Ten Bridesmaids'
      title: Parable of the Ten Bridesmaids
      number: 1
      content: "    <JESUS>\u201CThen the Kingdom of Heaven will be like ten bridesmaids</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>who took their lamps and went to meet the bridegroom.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '25:1 '
        content: '  Or   <b>virgins; </b>  also in 25:7, 11.  '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '<JESUS>Five of them were foolish, and five were wise.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "<JESUS>The five who were foolish didn\u2019t take enough olive oil
        for their lamps,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '<JESUS>but the other five were wise enough to take along extra oil.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '<JESUS>When the bridegroom was delayed, they all became drowsy and
        fell asleep.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CAt midnight they were roused by the shout, \u2018Look,
        the bridegroom is coming! Come out and meet him!\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CAll the bridesmaids got up and prepared their lamps.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>Then the five foolish ones asked the others, \u2018Please
        give us some of your oil because our lamps are going out.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBut the others replied, \u2018We don\u2019t have enough
        for all of us. Go to a shop and buy some for yourselves.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBut while they were gone to buy oil, the bridegroom
        came. Then those who were ready went in with him to the marriage feast, and
        the door was locked.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "<JESUS>Later, when the other five bridesmaids returned, they stood
        outside, calling, \u2018Lord! Lord! Open the door for us!\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBut he called back, \u2018Believe me, I don\u2019t
        know you!\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Parable of the Three Servants'
      title: Parable of the Three Servants
      number: 13
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CSo you, too, must keep watch! For you do not know
        the day or hour of my return.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CAgain, the Kingdom of Heaven can be illustrated by
        the story of a man going on a long trip. He called together his servants
        and entrusted his money to them while he was gone.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "<JESUS>He gave five bags of silver</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>to
        one, two bags of silver to another, and one bag of silver to the last\u2014dividing
        it in proportion to their abilities. He then left on his trip.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '25:15 '
        content: 'Greek <b>talents; </b>also throughout the story. A talent is equal
          to 75 pounds or 34 kilograms.  '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThe servant who received the five bags of silver began
        to invest the money and earned five more.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '<JESUS>The servant with two bags of silver also went to work and
        earned two more.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>But the servant who received the one bag of silver dug a hole
        in the ground and hid the master\u2019s money.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CAfter a long time their master returned from his trip
        and called them to give an account of how they had used his money.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>The servant to whom he had entrusted the five bags of silver
        came forward with five more and said, \u2018Master, you gave me five bags
        of silver to invest, and I have earned five more.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThe master was full of praise. \u2018Well done, my
        good and faithful servant. You have been faithful in handling this small
        amount, so now I will give you many more responsibilities. Let\u2019s celebrate
        together!</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '25:21 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>Enter into the joy of your master </b>  [or   <b>your
          Lord</b>  ]; also in 25:23.    '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThe servant who had received the two bags of silver
        came forward and said, \u2018Master, you gave me two bags of silver to invest,
        and I have earned two more.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThe master said, \u2018Well done, my good and faithful
        servant. You have been faithful in handling this small amount, so now I will
        give you many more responsibilities. Let\u2019s celebrate together!\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThen the servant with the one bag of silver came and
        said, \u2018Master, I knew you were a harsh man, harvesting crops you didn\u2019t
        plant and gathering crops you didn\u2019t cultivate.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "<JESUS>I was afraid I would lose your money, so I hid it in the earth.
        Look, here is your money back.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBut the master replied, \u2018You wicked and lazy
        servant! If you knew I harvested crops I didn\u2019t plant and gathered crops
        I didn\u2019t cultivate,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "<JESUS>why didn\u2019t you deposit my money in the bank? At least
        I could have gotten some interest on it.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThen he ordered, \u2018Take the money from this servant,
        and give it to the one with the ten bags of silver.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '<JESUS>To those who use well what they are given, even more will
        be given, and they will have an abundance. But from those who do nothing,
        even what little they have will be taken away.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: The Final Judgment'
      title: The Final Judgment
      number: 30
      content: "<JESUS>Now throw this useless servant into outer darkness, where
        there will be weeping and gnashing of teeth.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBut when the Son of Man</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>comes
        in his glory, and all the angels with him, then he will sit upon his glorious
        throne.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '25:31 '
        content: "  \u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself.  "
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: '<JESUS>All the nations</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>will be gathered
        in his presence, and he will separate the people as a shepherd separates
        the sheep from the goats.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '25:32 '
        content: 'Or <b>peoples.</b>  '
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: '<JESUS>He will place the sheep at his right hand and the goats at
        his left.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThen the King will say to those on his right, \u2018Come,
        you who are blessed by my Father, inherit the Kingdom prepared for you from
        the creation of the world.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: '<JESUS>For I was hungry, and you fed me. I was thirsty, and you gave
        me a drink. I was a stranger, and you invited me into your home.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "<JESUS>I was naked, and you gave me clothing. I was sick, and you
        cared for me. I was in prison, and you visited me.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThen these righteous ones will reply, \u2018Lord,
        when did we ever see you hungry and feed you? Or thirsty and give you something
        to drink?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: '<JESUS>Or a stranger and show you hospitality? Or naked and give
        you clothing?</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "<JESUS>When did we ever see you sick or in prison and visit you?\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CAnd the King will say, \u2018I tell you the truth,
        when you did it to one of the least of these my brothers and sisters,</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>you were doing it to me!\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '25:40 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>my brothers.</b>    '
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThen the King will turn to those on the left and say,
        \u2018Away with you, you cursed ones, into the eternal fire prepared for
        the devil and his demons.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '25:41 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>his angels.</b>  '
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "<JESUS>For I was hungry, and you didn\u2019t feed me. I was thirsty,
        and you didn\u2019t give me a drink.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "<JESUS>I was a stranger, and you didn\u2019t invite me into your
        home. I was naked, and you didn\u2019t give me clothing. I was sick and in
        prison, and you didn\u2019t visit me.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThen they will reply, \u2018Lord, when did we ever
        see you hungry or thirsty or a stranger or naked or sick or in prison, and
        not help you?\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CAnd he will answer, \u2018I tell you the truth, when
        you refused to help the least of these my brothers and sisters, you were
        refusing to help me.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CAnd they will go away into eternal punishment, but
        the righteous will go into eternal life.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Plot to Kill Jesus'
      title: The Plot to Kill Jesus
      number: 1
      content: '  When Jesus had finished saying all these things, he said to his
        disciples, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CAs you know, Passover begins in two days, and the Son
        of Man</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>will be handed over to be crucified.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '26:2 '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'At that same time the leading priests and elders were meeting at
        the residence of Caiaphas, the high priest, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'plotting how to capture Jesus secretly and kill him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Jesus Anointed at Bethany'
      title: Jesus Anointed at Bethany
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CBut not during the Passover celebration,\u201D they agreed,
        \u201Cor the people may riot.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Meanwhile, Jesus was in Bethany at the home of Simon, a man who had
        previously had leprosy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'While he was eating,[[COMMENT(0)]] a woman came in with a beautiful
        alabaster jar of expensive perfume and poured it over his head.  '
      comments:
      - number: '26:7 '
        content: Or <b>reclining.</b>
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The disciples were indignant when they saw this. \u201CWhat a waste!\u201D
        they said. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CIt could have been sold for a high price and the money given
        to the poor.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But Jesus, aware of this, replied, <JESUS>\u201CWhy criticize this
        woman for doing such a good thing to me?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '<JESUS>You will always have the poor among you, but you will not
        always have me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '<JESUS>She has poured this perfume on me to prepare my body for burial.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Judas Agrees to Betray Jesus'
      title: Judas Agrees to Betray Jesus
      number: 13
      content: "<JESUS>I tell you the truth, wherever the Good News is preached throughout
        the world, this woman\u2019s deed will be remembered and discussed.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then Judas Iscariot, one of the twelve disciples, went to the leading
        priests '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "and asked, \u201CHow much will you pay me to betray Jesus to you?\u201D
        And they gave him thirty pieces of silver. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: The Last Supper'
      title: The Last Supper
      number: 16
      content: 'From that time on, Judas began looking for an opportunity to betray
        Jesus.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "On the first day of the Festival of Unleavened Bread, the disciples
        came to Jesus and asked, \u201CWhere do you want us to prepare the Passover
        meal for you?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CAs you go into the city,\u201D </JESUS>he told them,
        <JESUS>\u201Cyou will see a certain man. Tell him, \u2018The Teacher says:
        My time has come, and I will eat the Passover meal with my disciples at your
        house.\u2019\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So the disciples did as Jesus told them and prepared the Passover
        meal there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'When it was evening, Jesus sat down at the table[[COMMENT(0)]] with
        the Twelve. '
      comments:
      - number: '26:20 '
        content: Or <b>Jesus reclined.</b>
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "While they were eating, he said, <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth,
        one of you will betray me.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Greatly distressed, each one asked in turn, \u201CAm I the one, Lord?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "He replied, <JESUS>\u201COne of you who has just eaten from this
        bowl with me will betray me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>For the Son of Man must die, as the Scriptures declared long
        ago. But how terrible it will be for the one who betrays him. It would be
        far better for that man if he had never been born!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Judas, the one who would betray him, also asked, \u201CRabbi, am
        I the one?\u201DAnd Jesus told him, <JESUS>\u201CYou have said it.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "As they were eating, Jesus took some bread and blessed it. Then he
        broke it in pieces and gave it to the disciples, saying, <JESUS>\u201CTake
        this and eat it, for this is my body.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And he took a cup of wine and gave thanks to God for it. He gave
        it to them and said, <JESUS>\u201CEach of you drink from it,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '<JESUS>for this is my blood, which confirms the covenant</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>between God and his people. It is poured out as a sacrifice to forgive
        the sins of many.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '26:28 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts read <b>the new covenant.</b>  '
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "<JESUS>Mark my words\u2014I will not drink wine again until the day
        I drink it new with you in my Father\u2019s Kingdom.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: "30: Jesus Predicts Peter\u2019s Denial"
      title: "Jesus Predicts Peter\u2019s Denial"
      number: 30
      content: 'Then they sang a hymn and went out to the Mount of Olives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "On the way, Jesus told them, <JESUS>\u201CTonight all of you will
        desert me. For the Scriptures say,</JESUS>  <JESUS>\u2018God will strike</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>the Shepherd,</JESUS>  <JESUS>and the sheep of the
        flock will be scattered.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '26:31 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>I will strike. </b>  Zech 13:7.  '
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "  <JESUS>But after I have been raised from the dead, I will go ahead
        of you to Galilee and meet you there.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Peter declared, \u201CEven if everyone else deserts you, I will never
        desert you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth, Peter\u2014this
        very night, before the rooster crows, you will deny three times that you
        even know me.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: Jesus Prays in Gethsemane'
      title: Jesus Prays in Gethsemane
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CNo!\u201D Peter insisted. \u201CEven if I have to die with
        you, I will never deny you!\u201D And all the other disciples vowed the same.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then Jesus went with them to the olive grove called Gethsemane, and
        he said, <JESUS>\u201CSit here while I go over there to pray.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "He took Peter and Zebedee\u2019s two sons, James and John, and he
        became anguished and distressed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "He told them, <JESUS>\u201CMy soul is crushed with grief to the point
        of death. Stay here and keep watch with me.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "He went on a little farther and bowed with his face to the ground,
        praying, <JESUS>\u201CMy Father! If it is possible, let this cup of suffering
        be taken away from me. Yet I want your will to be done, not mine.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Then he returned to the disciples and found them asleep. He said
        to Peter, <JESUS>\u201CCouldn\u2019t you watch with me even one hour?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "<JESUS>Keep watch and pray, so that you will not give in to temptation.
        For the spirit is willing, but the body is weak!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Then Jesus left them a second time and prayed, <JESUS>\u201CMy Father!
        If this cup cannot be taken away</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>unless I drink
        it, your will be done.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '26:42 '
        content: Greek <b>If this cannot pass.</b>
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "When he returned to them again, he found them sleeping, for they
        couldn\u2019t keep their eyes open.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'So he went to pray a third time, saying the same things again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "Then he came to the disciples and said, <JESUS>\u201CGo ahead and
        sleep. Have your rest. But look\u2014the time has come. The Son of Man is
        betrayed into the hands of sinners.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: Jesus Is Betrayed and Arrested'
      title: Jesus Is Betrayed and Arrested
      number: 46
      content: "<JESUS>Up, let\u2019s be going. Look, my betrayer is here!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'And even as Jesus said this, Judas, one of the twelve disciples,
        arrived with a crowd of men armed with swords and clubs. They had been sent
        by the leading priests and elders of the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "The traitor, Judas, had given them a prearranged signal: \u201CYou
        will know which one to arrest when I greet him with a kiss.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "So Judas came straight to Jesus. \u201CGreetings, Rabbi!\u201D he
        exclaimed and gave him the kiss.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CMy friend, go ahead and do what you have
        come for.\u201D</JESUS>Then the others grabbed Jesus and arrested him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "But one of the men with Jesus pulled out his sword and struck the
        high priest\u2019s slave, slashing off his ear.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CPut away your sword,\u201D </JESUS>Jesus told him.
        <JESUS>\u201CThose who use the sword will die by the sword.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "<JESUS>Don\u2019t you realize that I could ask my Father for thousands</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>of angels to protect us, and he would send them instantly?</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '26:53 '
        content: Greek <b>twelve legions.</b>
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "<JESUS>But if I did, how would the Scriptures be fulfilled that describe
        what must happen now?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: "Then Jesus said to the crowd, <JESUS>\u201CAm I some dangerous revolutionary,
        that you come with swords and clubs to arrest me? Why didn\u2019t you arrest
        me in the Temple? I was there teaching every day.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '56: Jesus before the Council'
      title: Jesus before the Council
      number: 56
      content: "<JESUS>But this is all happening to fulfill the words of the prophets
        as recorded in the Scriptures.\u201D</JESUS> At that point, all the disciples
        deserted him and fled.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'Then the people who had arrested Jesus led him to the home of Caiaphas,
        the high priest, where the teachers of religious law and the elders had gathered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "Meanwhile, Peter followed him at a distance and came to the high
        priest\u2019s courtyard. He went in and sat with the guards and waited to
        see how it would all end.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'Inside, the leading priests and the entire high council[[COMMENT(0)]]
        were trying to find witnesses who would lie about Jesus, so they could put
        him to death. '
      comments:
      - number: '26:59 '
        content: Greek <b>the Sanhedrin.</b>
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: "But even though they found many who agreed to give false witness,
        they could not use anyone\u2019s testimony. Finally, two men came forward "
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: "who declared, \u201CThis man said, \u2018I am able to destroy the
        Temple of God and rebuild it in three days.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: "Then the high priest stood up and said to Jesus, \u201CWell, aren\u2019t
        you going to answer these charges? What do you have to say for yourself?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: "But Jesus remained silent. Then the high priest said to him, \u201CI
        demand in the name of the living God\u2014tell us if you are the Messiah,
        the Son of God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CYou have said it. And in the future you
        will see the Son of Man seated in the place of power at God\u2019s right
        hand</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and coming on the clouds of heaven.\u201D</JESUS>[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '26:64a '
        content: Greek <b>seated at the right hand of the power. </b>See Ps 110:1.
      - number: '26:64b '
        content: See Dan 7:13.
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: "Then the high priest tore his clothing to show his horror and said,
        \u201CBlasphemy! Why do we need other witnesses? You have all heard his blasphemy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: "What is your verdict?\u201D\u201CGuilty!\u201D they shouted. \u201CHe
        deserves to die!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: "Then they began to spit in Jesus\u2019 face and beat him with their
        fists. And some slapped him, "
      comments: []
    - name: '68: Peter Denies Jesus'
      title: Peter Denies Jesus
      number: 68
      content: "jeering, \u201CProphesy to us, you Messiah! Who hit you that time?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '69: '
      title: 
      number: 69
      content: "Meanwhile, Peter was sitting outside in the courtyard. A servant
        girl came over and said to him, \u201CYou were one of those with Jesus the
        Galilean.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '70: '
      title: 
      number: 70
      content: "But Peter denied it in front of everyone. \u201CI don\u2019t know
        what you\u2019re talking about,\u201D he said.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '71: '
      title: 
      number: 71
      content: "Later, out by the gate, another servant girl noticed him and said
        to those standing around, \u201CThis man was with Jesus of Nazareth.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '26:71 '
        content: Or <b>Jesus the Nazarene.</b>
    - name: '72: '
      title: 
      number: 72
      content: "Again Peter denied it, this time with an oath. \u201CI don\u2019t
        even know the man,\u201D he said.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '73: '
      title: 
      number: 73
      content: "A little later some of the other bystanders came over to Peter and
        said, \u201CYou must be one of them; we can tell by your Galilean accent.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '74: '
      title: 
      number: 74
      content: "Peter swore, \u201CA curse on me if I\u2019m lying\u2014I don\u2019t
        know the man!\u201D And immediately the rooster crowed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '75: '
      title: 
      number: 75
      content: "Suddenly, Jesus\u2019 words flashed through Peter\u2019s mind: <JESUS>\u201CBefore
        the rooster crows, you will deny three times that you even know me.\u201D</JESUS>
        And he went away, weeping bitterly."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judas Hangs Himself'
      title: Judas Hangs Himself
      number: 1
      content: '  Very early in the morning the leading priests and the elders of
        the people met again to lay plans for putting Jesus to death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then they bound him, led him away, and took him to Pilate, the Roman
        governor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When Judas, who had betrayed him, realized that Jesus had been condemned
        to die, he was filled with remorse. So he took the thirty pieces of silver
        back to the leading priests and the elders. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CI have sinned,\u201D he declared, \u201Cfor I have betrayed
        an innocent man.\u201D\u201CWhat do we care?\u201D they retorted. \u201CThat\u2019s
        your problem.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Judas threw the silver coins down in the Temple and went out
        and hanged himself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The leading priests picked up the coins. \u201CIt wouldn\u2019t be
        right to put this money in the Temple treasury,\u201D they said, \u201Csince
        it was payment for murder.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '27:6 '
        content: Greek <b>since it is the price for blood.</b>
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "After some discussion they finally decided to buy the potter\u2019s
        field, and they made it into a cemetery for foreigners. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'That is why the field is still called the Field of Blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "This fulfilled the prophecy of Jeremiah that says,\u201CThey took[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the thirty pieces of silver\u2014the price at which he was valued by the
        people of Israel,  "
      comments:
      - number: '27:9 '
        content: Or <b>I took.</b>
    - name: "10: Jesus\u2019 Trial before Pilate"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 Trial before Pilate"
      number: 10
      content: "and purchased the potter\u2019s field,as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        directed.[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>Zech 11:12-13; Jer 32:6-9.</smallcaps>\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '27:9-10 '
        content: Greek <b>as the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>
          directed me. </b>
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now Jesus was standing before Pilate, the Roman governor. \u201CAre
        you the king of the Jews?\u201D the governor asked him.Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CYou
        have said it.\u201D </JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But when the leading priests and the elders made their accusations
        against him, Jesus remained silent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CDon\u2019t you hear all these charges they are bringing against
        you?\u201D Pilate demanded. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But Jesus made no response to any of the charges, much to the governor\u2019s
        surprise.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Now it was the governor\u2019s custom each year during the Passover
        celebration to release one prisoner to the crowd\u2014anyone they wanted. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'This year there was a notorious prisoner, a man named Barabbas.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '27:16 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>Jesus Barabbas; </b>also in 27:17.
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "As the crowds gathered before Pilate\u2019s house that morning, he
        asked them, \u201CWhich one do you want me to release to you\u2014Barabbas,
        or Jesus who is called the Messiah?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '(He knew very well that the religious leaders had arrested Jesus
        out of envy.)  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Just then, as Pilate was sitting on the judgment seat, his wife sent
        him this message: \u201CLeave that innocent man alone. I suffered through
        a terrible nightmare about him last night.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Meanwhile, the leading priests and the elders persuaded the crowd
        to ask for Barabbas to be released and for Jesus to be put to death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So the governor asked again, \u201CWhich of these two do you want
        me to release to you?\u201DThe crowd shouted back, \u201CBarabbas!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Pilate responded, \u201CThen what should I do with Jesus who is called
        the Messiah?\u201DThey shouted back, \u201CCrucify him!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CWhy?\u201D Pilate demanded. \u201CWhat crime has he committed?\u201DBut
        the mob roared even louder, \u201CCrucify him!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Pilate saw that he wasn\u2019t getting anywhere and that a riot was
        developing. So he sent for a bowl of water and washed his hands before the
        crowd, saying, \u201CI am innocent of this man\u2019s blood. The responsibility
        is yours!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And all the people yelled back, \u201CWe will take responsibility
        for his death\u2014we and our children!\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '27:25 '
        content: "Greek <b>\u201CHis blood be on us and on our children.\u201D</b>"
    - name: '26: The Soldiers Mock Jesus'
      title: The Soldiers Mock Jesus
      number: 26
      content: 'So Pilate released Barabbas to them. He ordered Jesus flogged with
        a lead-tipped whip, then turned him over to the Roman soldiers to be crucified.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Some of the governor\u2019s soldiers took Jesus into their headquarters[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and called out the entire regiment. "
      comments:
      - number: '27:27 '
        content: Or <b>into the Praetorium.</b>
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'They stripped him and put a scarlet robe on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "They wove thorn branches into a crown and put it on his head, and
        they placed a reed stick in his right hand as a scepter. Then they knelt
        before him in mockery and taunted, \u201CHail! King of the Jews!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And they spit on him and grabbed the stick and struck him on the
        head with it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: The Crucifixion'
      title: The Crucifixion
      number: 31
      content: 'When they were finally tired of mocking him, they took off the robe
        and put his own clothes on him again. Then they led him away to be crucified.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Along the way, they came across a man named Simon, who was from Cyrene,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and the soldiers forced him to carry Jesus\u2019 cross. "
      comments:
      - number: '27:32 '
        content: <b>Cyrene </b>was a city in northern Africa.
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And they went out to a place called Golgotha (which means \u201CPlace
        of the Skull\u201D). "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'The soldiers gave Jesus wine mixed with bitter gall, but when he
        had tasted it, he refused to drink it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'After they had nailed him to the cross, the soldiers gambled for
        his clothes by throwing dice.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '27:35 '
        content: "Greek <b>by casting lots. </b>A few late manuscripts add <b>This
          fulfilled the word of the prophet: \u201CThey divided my garments among
          themselves and cast lots for my robe.\u201D </b>See Ps 22:18."
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Then they sat around and kept guard as he hung there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "A sign was fastened above Jesus\u2019 head, announcing the charge
        against him. It read: \u201CThis is Jesus, the King of the Jews.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Two revolutionaries[[COMMENT(0)]] were crucified with him, one on
        his right and one on his left.  '
      comments:
      - number: '27:38 '
        content: Or <b>criminals; </b>also in 27:44.
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'The people passing by shouted abuse, shaking their heads in mockery. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "\u201CLook at you now!\u201D they yelled at him. \u201CYou said you
        were going to destroy the Temple and rebuild it in three days. Well then,
        if you are the Son of God, save yourself and come down from the cross!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'The leading priests, the teachers of religious law, and the elders
        also mocked Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "\u201CHe saved others,\u201D they scoffed, \u201Cbut he can\u2019t
        save himself! So he is the King of Israel, is he? Let him come down from
        the cross right now, and we will believe in him! "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "He trusted God, so let God rescue him now if he wants him! For he
        said, \u2018I am the Son of God.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: The Death of Jesus'
      title: The Death of Jesus
      number: 44
      content: 'Even the revolutionaries who were crucified with him ridiculed him
        in the same way.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "At noon, darkness fell across the whole land until three o\u2019clock. "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "At about three o\u2019clock, Jesus called out with a loud voice,
        <JESUS>\u201CEli, Eli,</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>lema sabachthani?\u201D</JESUS>
        which means <JESUS>\u201CMy God, my God, why have you abandoned me?\u201D</JESUS>[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '27:46a '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>Eloi, Eloi.</b>
      - number: '27:46b '
        content: Ps 22:1.
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Some of the bystanders misunderstood and thought he was calling for
        the prophet Elijah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'One of them ran and filled a sponge with sour wine, holding it up
        to him on a reed stick so he could drink. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "But the rest said, \u201CWait! Let\u2019s see whether Elijah comes
        to save him.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '27:49 '
        content: Some manuscripts add <b>And another took a spear and pierced his
          side, and out flowed water and blood. </b>Compare John 19:34.
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Then Jesus shouted out again, and he released his spirit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'At that moment the curtain in the sanctuary of the Temple was torn
        in two, from top to bottom. The earth shook, rocks split apart, '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'and tombs opened. The bodies of many godly men and women who had
        died were raised from the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "They left the cemetery after Jesus\u2019 resurrection, went into
        the holy city of Jerusalem, and appeared to many people.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "The Roman officer[[COMMENT(0)]] and the other soldiers at the crucifixion
        were terrified by the earthquake and all that had happened. They said, \u201CThis
        man truly was the Son of God!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '27:54 '
        content: Greek <b>The centurion.</b>
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'And many women who had come from Galilee with Jesus to care for him
        were watching from a distance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: The Burial of Jesus'
      title: The Burial of Jesus
      number: 56
      content: 'Among them were Mary Magdalene, Mary (the mother of James and Joseph),
        and the mother of James and John, the sons of Zebedee.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'As evening approached, Joseph, a rich man from Arimathea who had
        become a follower of Jesus, '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "went to Pilate and asked for Jesus\u2019 body. And Pilate issued
        an order to release it to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'Joseph took the body and wrapped it in a long sheet of clean linen
        cloth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: 'He placed it in his own new tomb, which had been carved out of the
        rock. Then he rolled a great stone across the entrance and left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '61: The Guard at the Tomb'
      title: The Guard at the Tomb
      number: 61
      content: 'Both Mary Magdalene and the other Mary were sitting across from the
        tomb and watching.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'The next day, on the Sabbath,[[COMMENT(0)]] the leading priests and
        Pharisees went to see Pilate. '
      comments:
      - number: '27:62 '
        content: Or <b>On the next day, which is after the Preparation.</b>
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: "They told him, \u201CSir, we remember what that deceiver once said
        while he was still alive: \u2018After three days I will rise from the dead.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: "So we request that you seal the tomb until the third day. This will
        prevent his disciples from coming and stealing his body and then telling
        everyone he was raised from the dead! If that happens, we\u2019ll be worse
        off than we were at first.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: "Pilate replied, \u201CTake guards and secure it the best you can.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: So they sealed the tomb and posted guards to protect it.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Resurrection'
      title: The Resurrection
      number: 1
      content: '  Early on Sunday morning,[[COMMENT(0)]] as the new day was dawning,
        Mary Magdalene and the other Mary went out to visit the tomb.  '
      comments:
      - number: '28:1 '
        content: Greek <b>After the Sabbath, on the first day of the week.</b>
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Suddenly there was a great earthquake! For an angel of the Lord came
        down from heaven, rolled aside the stone, and sat on it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'His face shone like lightning, and his clothing was as white as snow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The guards shook with fear when they saw him, and they fell into
        a dead faint.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the angel spoke to the women. \u201CDon\u2019t be afraid!\u201D
        he said. \u201CI know you are looking for Jesus, who was crucified. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He isn\u2019t here! He is risen from the dead, just as he said would
        happen. Come, see where his body was lying. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And now, go quickly and tell his disciples that he has risen from
        the dead, and he is going ahead of you to Galilee. You will see him there.
        Remember what I have told you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The women ran quickly from the tomb. They were very frightened but
        also filled with great joy, and they rushed to give the disciples the angel\u2019s
        message. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And as they went, Jesus met them and greeted them. And they ran to
        him, grasped his feet, and worshiped him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Report of the Guard'
      title: The Report of the Guard
      number: 10
      content: "Then Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t be afraid! Go tell
        my brothers to leave for Galilee, and they will see me there.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'As the women were on their way, some of the guards went into the
        city and told the leading priests what had happened. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'A meeting with the elders was called, and they decided to give the
        soldiers a large bribe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "They told the soldiers, \u201CYou must say, \u2018Jesus\u2019 disciples
        came during the night while we were sleeping, and they stole his body.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "If the governor hears about it, we\u2019ll stand up for you so you
        won\u2019t get in trouble.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Great Commission'
      title: The Great Commission
      number: 15
      content: 'So the guards accepted the bribe and said what they were told to
        say. Their story spread widely among the Jews, and they still tell it today.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then the eleven disciples left for Galilee, going to the mountain
        where Jesus had told them to go. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "When they saw him, they worshiped him\u2014but some of them doubted!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Jesus came and told his disciples, <JESUS>\u201CI have been given
        all authority in heaven and on earth.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '<JESUS>Therefore, go and make disciples of all the nations,</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>baptizing them in the name of the Father and the Son and the Holy
        Spirit.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '28:19 '
        content: Or <b>all peoples.</b>
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>Teach these new disciples to obey all the commands I have
        given you. And be sure of this: I am with you always, even to the end of
        the age.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
